Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.20,0:07:24.44,越南语,,0,0,1,,已经40年过去了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:33.06,越南语,,0,0,1,,但是越南的老兵们
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.87,0:07:36.12,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们也不想谈论那场战争
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:41.40,越南语,,0,0,1,,人们歌颂胜利 歌颂自由 他们都错了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.83,0:07:45.71,越南语,,0,0,1,,谁赢谁输并不重要
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.34,0:07:49.76,越南语,,0,0,1,,在战争中没有赢家或输家
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.72,0:07:54.45,越南语,,0,0,1,,只有破坏和毁灭
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.76,0:07:58.31,越南语,,0,0,1,,只有那些没打过仗的人们
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.35,0:08:01.88,越南语,,0,0,1,,才喜欢争论谁赢谁输
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.06,0:08:48.48,越南语,,0,0,1,,法国在19世纪中期攻占了我们的国家
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.52,0:08:53.32,越南语,,0,0,1,,那场入侵既血腥又残酷
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:08.56,越南语,,0,0,1,,法国人当然自夸自擂于
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:13.15,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们为越南人民所带来的文明
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.25,0:10:15.86,越南语,,0,0,1,,越南人当然不需要法国的文明
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.07,0:10:19.49,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们需要的是独立
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.56,0:10:46.10,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们控制了一切
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.60,0:10:49.81,越南语,,0,0,1,,控制我们国家的一切资源
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:54.80,越南语,,0,0,1,,但最重要的是 他们夺走了我们的独立
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:56.30,越南语,,0,0,1,,夺走了我们的自由
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.53,0:11:03.32,越南语,,0,0,1,,当我还是小孩时 我就已在学校里萌生了民族主义
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.91,0:11:07.45,越南语,,0,0,1,,我总是将法国人视作敌人
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.21,0:11:10.54,越南语,,0,0,1,,我的敌人
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:16.80,越南语,,0,0,1,,对法国人来说 越南人就是一个次等民族
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.80,0:11:22.66,越南语,,0,0,1,,在越南 没有平等可言
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.26,0:11:26.43,越南语,,0,0,1,,所以我们才如此痛恨他们
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.95,0:18:07.50,越南语,,0,0,1,,每个人都想加入越盟参战
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.88,0:18:11.96,越南语,,0,0,1,,大多数人都不知道越盟
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.96,0:18:14.67,越南语,,0,0,1,,是一个共产主义组织
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.54,0:22:23.17,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们看到美国人来了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.84,0:22:26.47,越南语,,0,0,1,,当我们看到美国人时
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.63,0:22:30.72,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们把他们看作自由人
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.18,0:22:32.76,越南语,,0,0,1,,来解放人们
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.14,0:22:35.89,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们已经解放过欧洲了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.62,0:25:42.62,越南语,,0,0,1,,所有的越南人 不只是我
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.75,0:25:47.75,越南语,,0,0,1,,都觉得从今往后越南都将独立
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.79,0:25:51.17,越南语,,0,0,1,,自由 统一 领土完整
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.09,0:25:54.67,越南语,,0,0,1,,在世界地图上也有正式的名字
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.76,0:25:57.01,越南语,,0,0,1,,每个人都很自豪
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.10,0:34:05.00,越南语,,0,0,1,,我看到越盟杀死了自己的越南同胞
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.04,0:34:09.84,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们不是真的为越南人而战
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.88,0:34:12.67,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们只为国际共产体系而战
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.67,0:35:13.82,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们有种强烈的责任感要去为国家而战
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.03,0:35:23.95,越南语,,0,0,1,,在我的记忆里那是一段开心美好的时光
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.37,0:35:31.42,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们在前去战斗时还都唱着歌
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.46,0:35:32.96,越南语,,0,0,1,,那些很浪漫的歌
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.38,0:38:23.67,越南语,,0,0,1,,1948年 在我的家乡
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.88,0:38:27.09,越南语,,0,0,1,,法国人开着坦克进来
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.34,0:38:30.60,越南语,,0,0,1,,烧了我们的房屋
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.97,0:38:35.56,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们用来犁田的水牛
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.60,0:38:37.52,越南语,,0,0,1,,很多都被他们开枪打死了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.85,0:38:42.40,越南语,,0,0,1,,那时我还是个小孩
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.44,0:38:46.61,越南语,,0,0,1,,我看见了那一幕
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.86,0:38:52.29,越南语,,0,0,1,,那场景就烙印在我的记忆里
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.75,0:39:39.25,越南语,,0,0,1,,我看到越盟
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.37,0:39:44.67,越南语,,0,0,1,,逮捕了效力法国军队的越南士兵
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.80,0:39:48.53,越南语,,0,0,1,,把他们脱光
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.76,0:39:52.60,越南语,,0,0,1,,然后残酷地杀死他们
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.64,0:39:54.93,越南语,,0,0,1,,把他们活活烧死
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.81,0:39:59.73,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们不想浪费子弹在这些人身上
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.56,0:40:06.03,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们生活在两方压迫者之下
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.89,0:56:09.86,越南语,,0,0,1,,奠边府的胜利解放了我们半个国家
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.16,0:56:14.20,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们消灭了一整支法国军队
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.70,0:56:20.80,越南语,,0,0,1,,这次胜利让我们更自信了
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.02,0:59:24.52,越南语,,0,0,1,,日内瓦协议规定了在两年内举行大选
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.60,0:59:26.60,越南语,,0,0,1,,以重新统一国家
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.92,0:59:28.52,越南语,,0,0,1,,大家都相信了
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.23,0:59:33.40,越南语,,0,0,1,,没人想到它会持续20多年
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.86,0:59:39.03,越南语,,0,0,1,,我到北越接受训练
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.20,0:59:41.66,越南语,,0,0,1,,为的就是有天能解放南部
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.04,0:59:46.21,越南语,,0,0,1,,但我怎么也想不到战争会如此残酷
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.75,0:59:48.96,越南语,,0,0,1,,那种残暴难以想象
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.04,1:10:55.75,越南语,,0,0,1,,当时我们没有枪
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.97,1:10:59.13,越南语,,0,0,1,,所以我们用砍刀去杀那些暴政者
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.67,1:11:02.13,越南语,,0,0,1,,在起义中
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.17,1:11:04.43,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们杀死了一名安全官员
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.84,1:11:10.06,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们12个人都拿着砍刀
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.89,1:11:14.02,越南语,,0,0,1,,他跑走掉进了稻田里
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.77,1:11:16.02,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们就把他砍死了
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.44,1:11:20.03,越南语,,0,0,1,,然后我们告诉人们
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.23,1:11:22.74,越南语,,0,0,1,,如果有人敢去参加他的葬礼
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.15,1:11:24.99,越南语,,0,0,1,,那也会被我们杀死
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.41,1:11:28.99,越南语,,0,0,1,,所以就没人敢去了
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.46,1:12:25.59,越南语,,0,0,1,,我第一次见到黎筍是在1951年
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.22,1:12:29.47,越南语,,0,0,1,,我当时是个小干部
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.26,1:12:34.56,越南语,,0,0,1,,我看到他和其他领导人很不一样
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.17,1:12:41.11,越南语,,0,0,1,,他能理解南方同志们的意愿
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.94,1:12:49.57,越南语,,0,0,1,,黎筍把他们的意愿带回了北方
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.70,1:13:21.10,越南语,,0,0,1,,北越采取了更为攻势的姿态
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.77,1:13:26.36,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们不接受国家这样子的分裂
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.32,1:13:30.72,越南语,,0,0,1,,他们想要这个国家
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.78,1:13:32.20,越南语,,0,0,1,,重新统一
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.66,1:13:34.08,越南语,,0,0,1,,且不惜一切代价
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.38,1:17:16.17,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们的领导人说 "我们愿意牺牲至最后一名越南人"
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.34,1:17:20.39,越南语,,0,0,1,,我们为这些口号而欢欣鼓舞
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.93,1:17:27.60,越南语,,0,0,1,,人们没有完全理解
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.73,1:17:32.31,越南语,,0,0,1,,在这些英雄口号的背后
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.11,1:17:34.98,越南语,,0,0,1,,将是他们自己的牺牲
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.03,1:17:40.32,越南语,,0,0,1,,历史自会评判这场战争
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.41,1:17:42.87,越南语,,0,0,1,,是否值得这么多的牺牲
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.67,0:00:56.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Coming home from Vietnam was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.77,0:01:00.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,close to as traumatic as the war itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.67,0:01:04.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For years, nobody talked about Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.33,0:01:09.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were friends with a young couple
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.03,0:01:14.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and it was only after 12 years that the two wives were talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.23,0:01:17.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Found out that we both had been Marines in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.62,0:01:19.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Never said a word about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.96,0:01:21.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Never mentioned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.99,0:01:24.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the whole country was like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.35,0:01:27.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was so divisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.14,0:01:32.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it's like living in a family with an alcoholic father.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.04,0:01:36.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Shh, we don't talk about that."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.26,0:01:40.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Our country did that with Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.06,0:01:42.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It's only been very recently that, I think, that,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.94,0:01:45.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,you know, the baby boomers are finally starting to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.62,0:01:47.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.62,0:01:49.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,What happened?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.10,0:02:00.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,What we need now in this country
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:02.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,is to heal the wounds
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.88,0:02:05.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and to put Vietnam behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.14,0:02:20.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The killing in this tragic war must stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.45,0:02:33.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Westmoreland's strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.52,0:02:35.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,is producing results.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:39.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The enemy is no longer closer to victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:48.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,No matter how you measure it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.49,0:02:52.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we're better off than we thought we would be at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.66,0:02:59.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have been less than candid
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.66,0:03:03.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as to how deeply we are involved in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:05.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We have increased our assistance
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.64,0:03:07.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to the government, its logistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:09.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We have not sent combat troops there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:13.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have a row of dominoes set up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.45,0:03:16.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and you knock over the first one and the last one,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:17.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,certainly it will go over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.59,0:03:19.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If aggression is successful in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.73,0:03:22.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we can expect it to spread throughout Asia and Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.95,0:03:24.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and to this hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:04:03.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Viktor Frankl, who survived the death camps in World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.22,0:04:05.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,wrote a book called Man's Search for Meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:10.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You know, "To live is to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.46,0:04:14.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To survive is to find meaning in suffering."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:19.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And for those of us who suffered because of Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.11,0:04:24.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that's been our quest ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.83,0:04:41.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,America's involvement in Vietnam began in secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.37,0:04:47.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It ended, 30 years later, in failure,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.02,0:04:49.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,witnessed by the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.32,0:04:56.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was begun in good faith by decent people
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.59,0:04:59.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,out of fateful misunderstandings,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.25,0:05:03.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American overconfidence, and Cold War miscalculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.84,0:05:06.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was prolonged
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.26,0:05:09.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because it seemed easier to muddle through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:12.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,than admit that it had been caused by tragic decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.11,0:05:15.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,made by five American presidents,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:18.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,belonging to both political parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.68,0:05:22.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Before the war was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.32,0:05:26.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,more than 58,000 Americans would be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.96,0:05:30.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,At least 250,000 South Vietnamese troops
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:33.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,died in the conflict, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:37.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So did over a million North Vietnamese soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:39.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and Viet Cong guerrillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:47.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Two million civilians, north and south,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.81,0:05:49.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,are thought to have perished,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.50,0:05:51.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as well as tens of thousands more
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:55.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in the neighboring states of Laos and Cambodia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:05:59.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For many Vietnamese,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.36,0:06:01.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,it was a brutal civil war;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:05.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for others, the bloody climactic chapter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.29,0:06:08.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a century-old struggle for independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.28,0:06:16.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For those Americans who fought in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:19.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and for those who fought against it back home,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:23.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as well as for those who merely glimpsed it on the nightly news,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.80,0:06:27.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Vietnam War was a decade of agony,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:31.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the most divisive period since the Civil War.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.81,0:06:37.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam seemed to call everything into question...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.65,0:06:41.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the value of honor and gallantry;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.03,0:06:45.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the qualities of cruelty and mercy;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.83,0:06:50.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the candor of the American government;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.65,0:06:55.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and what it means to be a patriot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.03,0:07:03.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And those who lived through it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.95,0:07:06.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,have never been able to erase its memory,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.77,0:07:09.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,have never stopped arguing about what really happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.33,0:07:13.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,why everything went so badly wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.33,0:07:14.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who was to blame,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:18.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and whether it was all worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.77,0:08:58.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French conquest of Indochina began with
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.73,0:09:03.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,an attack on the ancient Vietnamese port of Danang in 1858.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.93,0:09:08.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It took 50 years to lay claim to the whole region...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.60,0:09:10.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Laos and Cambodia,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.28,0:09:13.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as well as the 1,200-mile-long area
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.54,0:09:16.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that would come to be called Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.37,0:09:22.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,All of it was ruled by a French governor-general
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:24.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from his palace in Hanoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.07,0:09:29.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French largely lived on plantation estates,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:32.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and in cities, like Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:35.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,made to look as much as possible like those at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:40.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Most did not even bother to learn the language
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.61,0:09:42.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,spoken by their subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.34,0:09:46.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Instead they installed a series of puppet emperors
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:51.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and employed a network of French-speaking Vietnamese officials...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.12,0:09:52.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,mandarins...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.21,0:09:54.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,willing to carry out their wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.40,0:09:59.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French put their subjects to work
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.98,0:10:02.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,building roads and canals,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:04.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,railroads and bridges.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.70,0:10:25.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Vietnamese people did not take easily to French occupation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.17,0:10:29.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,just as they had fought against earlier invasions by the Chinese.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.89,0:10:34.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By the early 20th century, nationalism was on the rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:37.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But anyone who dared resist colonial rule
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.71,0:10:41.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,risked exile, prison, or the guillotine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.86,0:11:38.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My hatred for them was pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.62,0:11:40.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:42.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I hated them so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.44,0:11:45.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I was so scared of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.88,0:11:52.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Boy, I was terrified of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.81,0:12:03.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the scareder I got, the more I hated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.52,0:12:09.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I was an 18-year-old Marine rifleman
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.23,0:12:11.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with the ink still wet on my high school diploma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:14.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to shame myself in front of my buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.74,0:12:18.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But I was so scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.97,0:12:21.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I felt like I was hanging onto my honor by my fingernails
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.88,0:12:23.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the whole time I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:40.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the Spring of 1919,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:43.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as the victorious Allied Powers met in Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:47.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to rebuild a world shattered by the Great War,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:51.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Woodrow Wilson headed the American delegation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:53.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,housed in the Hotel Crillon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:13:00.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,One day, a tall, slender, 29-year-old man
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.24,0:13:02.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,appeared with a petition for the president
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:06.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he and other Vietnamese nationalists had written.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.86,0:13:10.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Inspired by Wilson's declaration
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.30,0:13:13.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the interests of colonial peoples should be given
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.45,0:13:16.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,equal weight with those of their European rulers,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.03,0:13:21.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the man was asking that this principle be applied to his homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.03,0:13:26.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The president's secretary promised to show it to Wilson,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.79,0:13:29.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but there is no evidence that he ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:33.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,His name was Nguyen Tat Thanh,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.05,0:13:37.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but he was now living under an alias, Nguyen Ai Quoc...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.67,0:13:39.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Nguyen the Patriot."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.16,0:13:43.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,During his long, shadowy career,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.26,0:13:46.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he would adopt some 70 different pseudonyms,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.19,0:13:50.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,finally settling on "the most enlightened one"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.45,0:13:52.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.49,0:13:56.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was a man who
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:13:59.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,succeeded in projecting an image of somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.79,0:14:05.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who was totally dedicated to freeing his country and his people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:07.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from foreign domination
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:12.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to the point that he sacrificed his own well-being, his own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.99,0:14:15.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,not having a family of his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.15,0:14:19.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To Vietnamese, that's a big sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:23.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because to us everybody needs a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:26.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was born in 1890,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.99,0:14:30.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the son of a minor official in the French regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.04,0:14:34.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,After taking part in a demonstration against the puppet emperor
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:37.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the Frenchmen who pulled his strings,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.47,0:14:41.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho was expelled from school and marked for arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.85,0:14:48.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He left Vietnam in 1911 and remained in exile for 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.13,0:14:53.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He served as a cook's helper aboard a French liner,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:14:56.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and visited New York and Boston,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.14,0:15:00.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where he worked for a time as a pastry chef at the Parker House.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.36,0:15:03.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He shoveled snow in London,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.20,0:15:06.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,tinted photographs in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:11.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There, Ho Chi Minh joined the French Socialist Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.08,0:15:15.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But when he discovered the anti-colonial writings of Lenin,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:17.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he became a communist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.94,0:15:21.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He was invited to Moscow to study,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:24.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,underwent training as a Soviet agent,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.12,0:15:28.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was sometimes criticized for being a nationalist first,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:29.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a communist second,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:32.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and then was dispatched to China
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.58,0:15:36.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to organize a cell of other Vietnamese exiles
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.11,0:15:40.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and help establish the Indochinese Communist Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.77,0:15:42.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Through it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.86,0:15:44.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"He was taut and quivering,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:45.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a friend remembered,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.86,0:15:47.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"with only one thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:50.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,his country, Vietnam."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:10.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By 1940, much of the world was at war again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.22,0:16:21.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Germany had seized most of Western Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.76,0:16:23.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including France.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:28.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Imperial Japan threatened
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:31.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,many of the European colonies in Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.07,0:16:33.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and occupied Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.06,0:16:36.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where they permitted their allies, the collaborationist French,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:39.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to continue to oversee their colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:44.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To some Vietnamese,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:47.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the coming of the Japanese seemed to signal
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.18,0:16:50.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a welcome end to white colonial rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:54.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Ho Chi Minh, still in exile in China,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.38,0:16:57.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,saw the Japanese as alien invaders,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.40,0:16:59.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,no more welcome than the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.41,0:17:03.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were only interested in exploiting his country
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:08.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and seizing Vietnamese crops to fill their own rice bowls.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.96,0:17:11.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The time had come, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.61,0:17:15.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to rally "patriots of all ages and all types,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:19.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,peasants, workers, merchants and soldiers"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:23.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to defeat the Japanese and the collaborationist French.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.94,0:17:29.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In February of 1941,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.48,0:17:32.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,after three decades away from his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.24,0:17:36.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh slipped back across the Chinese border into Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.86,0:17:41.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and set up headquarters near the remote village of Pac Bo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:44.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a limestone cave at the side of a mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.11,0:17:46.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he named for Karl Marx,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.15,0:17:51.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,overlooking a jungle stream he named for his hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.25,0:17:52.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Lenin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:57.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There, he founded a revolutionary movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.19,0:18:00.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,which he called the Vietnam Independence League...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.09,0:18:02.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.29,0:18:19.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To build and lead a fighting force for his revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.64,0:18:22.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho called upon Vo Nguyen Giap,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:24.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a one-time teacher of French history
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.93,0:18:28.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had instructed the children of Hanoi's elite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.45,0:18:32.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Giap was an early convert to communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.19,0:18:35.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whose life-long hatred for the French intensified
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.60,0:18:38.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,when they beat his wife to death in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:43.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Inspired by Napoleon, Lawrence of Arabia,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.56,0:18:47.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the communist Chinese revolutionary Mao Zedong,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:51.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Giap had already begun to develop a distinctive theory of warfare
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.97,0:18:54.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that relied on guerrilla tactics
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.64,0:18:58.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,until a full-scale conventional attack could be mounted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.85,0:19:03.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the fight for independence which he believed was coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:09.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,his armies, Giap said, would be "everywhere and nowhere."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.04,0:19:14.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The reason Vietnamese had always resort to guerrilla warfare
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:16.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was because we were a small country.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.39,0:19:20.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was just a way of fight the weak against the strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.32,0:19:25.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Don't fight unless you're sure you can win,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:29.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and surprise is a big element.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:32.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Choose your own battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.92,0:19:43.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I had about 26 guys that day out of 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.38,0:19:45.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were always somewhat understrength.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.68,0:19:48.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And this day we were quite understrength.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.82,0:19:51.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My platoon's on point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:19:58.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Go, go, go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:20:01.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden the very point man,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:03.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the first guy in the column,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.12,0:20:06.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,said, "VC on the trail. VC on the trail."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.29,0:20:11.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Before I had a chance to digest this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.19,0:20:13.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,... he went down, shot right through the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.41,0:20:19.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And what was a very well-laid ambush erupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.76,0:20:32.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I knew I'd lost a bunch of guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:34.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I said a prayer to God
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.03,0:20:36.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.42,0:20:39.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,basically, "If you need any more guys from my platoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:41.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,take me. Don't take any more of my men."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:42.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As soon as I said it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.53,0:20:45.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I freaked myself out and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.02,0:20:48.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Holy shit. Can I take that prayer back?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.39,0:21:02.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By the Spring of 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.43,0:21:07.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,more than three years after the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.37,0:21:11.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the United States government was looking for allies
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.51,0:21:13.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,behind the lines in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.72,0:21:15.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Americans were hoping to find a way
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.81,0:21:18.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to undermine Japanese forces there
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.01,0:21:21.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,when they were contacted by Ho Chi Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.79,0:21:26.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And so it was decided to drop an OSS team in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.83,0:21:29.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to meet with the Viet Minh leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:34.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Paul Hoagland was the medic on the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.26,0:21:37.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the first thing he was told was that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:40.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he must attend to their leader, who was desperately sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.53,0:21:43.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So he was taken to a grass shack
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.78,0:21:48.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where a bewhiskered, skinny man lay on a bundle of straw,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.58,0:21:49.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,desperately ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.41,0:21:51.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And that was Ho Chi Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:58.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The OSS, the secret wartime precursor of the CIA,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.67,0:22:02.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,supplied Ho's ragtag guerrillas with arms
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:05.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and marveled at how quickly they learned to handle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.95,0:22:09.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh began to call his followers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.60,0:22:11.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the "Viet-American Army,"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.02,0:22:15.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and praised the United States as a "champion of democracy"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.87,0:22:19.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that would surely help them end colonial rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:41.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, famine gripped the northern part of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.96,0:22:46.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of thousands of Vietnamese were dying of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.20,0:22:50.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,while Japanese storehouses were filled with rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.61,0:22:56.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In those days, garbage was collected by people pushing carts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:23:00.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And my mother remembers that every morning
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.58,0:23:03.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,she would see these garbage carts going around
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.65,0:23:07.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and people picking up dead bodies and throwing them on the cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.97,0:23:09.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:13.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And people who lived through it never, never forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.85,0:23:19.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Duong Van Mai's father was the deputy governor of a province east of Hanoi,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.43,0:23:24.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the son and grandson of mandarins who had all served the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.86,0:23:27.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He and his wife had 17 children.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.66,0:23:33.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Parents who had children who were, you know, plump,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.13,0:23:37.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were very afraid of their children being stolen and killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.19,0:23:41.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was really like hell on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:46.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The government didn't have a clue on how to deal with this calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.63,0:23:50.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Ho Chi Minh did.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.39,0:23:52.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He directed the Viet Minh to break
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.56,0:23:55.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into the Japanese storehouses wherever they could
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.96,0:23:58.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and distribute the rice to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.96,0:24:02.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were hailed as saviors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.39,0:24:20.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,When an atomic bomb destroyed Hiroshima,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.80,0:24:24.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and three days later a second one destroyed Nagasaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.92,0:24:27.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Japanese surrender seemed imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.36,0:24:33.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh called upon all Vietnamese to rise up
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.12,0:24:35.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and take over their own country
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.25,0:24:37.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,before the Free French could reestablish
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.88,0:24:40.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,their old colonial regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.27,0:24:45.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They did, in cities and towns across the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.76,0:24:51.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On September 2, 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.76,0:24:55.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the same day the Japanese formally surrendered,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.36,0:25:00.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hundreds of thousands of Vietnamese streamed into Ba Dinh Square in Hanoi
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.85,0:25:05.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to see for the first time the mysterious leader of the Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.96,0:25:10.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and hear him proclaim Vietnam's independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.50,0:25:18.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,With an OSS officer standing nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.69,0:25:23.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh began with the words of Thomas Jefferson:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.04,0:25:25.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"All men are created equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.60,0:25:31.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They are endowed by their creator with certain unalienable rights;
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.63,0:25:34.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that among these are life, liberty
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.12,0:25:37.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the pursuit of happiness."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.65,0:26:01.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh had great hopes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.78,0:26:06.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the U.S. would support the Vietnam desire for independence,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.86,0:26:09.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,not necessarily by intervening
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.83,0:26:12.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but by doing what it could
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.88,0:26:15.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to support an independence movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.57,0:26:20.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh's hopes for American support were calculated
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.69,0:26:22.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.62,0:26:27.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Franklin Roosevelt had promised a postwar world
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.37,0:26:30.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that would "respect the rights of all peoples
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.28,0:26:33.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to choose the form of government under which they live."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.29,0:26:38.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Roosevelt was dead now,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.22,0:26:40.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and his successor, Harry Truman,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.60,0:26:43.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,had inherited a very different world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.60,0:26:47.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The alliance with the Soviet Union that had
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.05,0:26:50.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,won the Second World War had collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.55,0:26:52.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Soviets now occupied the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.89,0:26:55.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Eastern European countries they had overrun,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.83,0:26:58.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and hoped to spread their influence farther,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.69,0:27:02.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into Iran, Turkey, and the Mediterranean.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.91,0:27:06.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A new cold war had begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.33,0:27:10.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French president Charles De Gaulle warned
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.91,0:27:13.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that if the United States insisted
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.21,0:27:15.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on independence for her colonies,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.76,0:27:17.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,France might have no choice
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.68,0:27:20.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but to "fall into the Russian orbit."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.01,0:27:24.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States must do nothing to undercut
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.74,0:27:27.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the restoration of France's empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.90,0:27:30.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.05,0:27:37.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There were hardly any Americans in Vietnam, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.55,0:27:39.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,State Department people,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.22,0:27:40.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,consular officials,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.91,0:27:43.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a few businessmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.17,0:27:45.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Hardly anyone from this country
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.43,0:27:47.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,knew where Vietnam was located.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.05,0:27:51.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,George Wickes was part of a seven-man OSS mission
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.92,0:27:55.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,sent to Saigon, the largest city in the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.26,0:27:58.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States was officially neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.86,0:28:01.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hoping the French and Viet Minh could reach
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.49,0:28:04.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,some peaceful solution on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.22,0:28:09.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Allied leaders had agreed temporarily to divide Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.16,0:28:11.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into two separate zones.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.47,0:28:15.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Nationalist Chinese troops were to handle things in the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.81,0:28:20.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,British colonial troops would try to perform the same task in the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.01,0:28:25.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where rival factions, including the French and Viet Minh,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.15,0:28:28.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were already fighting in the streets of Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.19,0:28:32.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,No one was in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.56,0:28:37.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On both sides, there was brutality and atrocity and violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.86,0:28:40.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It wasn't quite a civil war
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.50,0:28:44.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but it was getting very close to civil war in the streets of Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.86,0:28:49.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonel Peter Dewey, the 28-year-old
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.09,0:28:51.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,commander of the OSS in Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.73,0:28:53.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,tried to make sense of it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.15,0:28:57.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Right from the start he was in touch with everybody...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.14,0:28:58.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,not only the French,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.35,0:29:01.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but very soon he established a connection with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.18,0:29:03.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,various Vietnamese groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.76,0:29:06.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Viet Minh soon established themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.63,0:29:08.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as the most successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.27,0:29:12.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Dewey, who spoke fluent French,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.71,0:29:15.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,brokered talks between a Viet Minh spokesman
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.81,0:29:18.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the senior French representative in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.28,0:29:24.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,His efforts infuriated British general Douglas Gracey,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.20,0:29:26.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who commanded Allied forces in the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.68,0:29:30.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Gracey was convinced that French control
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.32,0:29:33.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,should be reimposed as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.57,0:29:36.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By conferring with the Viet Minh, Gracey said,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.56,0:29:40.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Colonel Dewey had become a "subversive" force.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.32,0:29:46.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The violence in and around Saigon escalated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.66,0:29:50.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Colonel Dewey urgently cabled his superiors:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.81,0:29:54.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam "is burning," he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.59,0:29:57.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"The French and British are finished here
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.24,0:30:02.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the United States," he concluded, "ought to clear out of Southeast Asia."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.23,0:30:07.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Two days later,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.75,0:30:10.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,September 26, 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.19,0:30:13.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he set out for the airport,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.31,0:30:16.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,prepared to fly to OSS headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.46,0:30:19.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,At a roadblock,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.78,0:30:23.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Viet Minh mistook Dewey for a Frenchman
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.11,0:30:24.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and opened fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.43,0:30:28.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He was killed instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.26,0:30:33.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh wrote to the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.85,0:30:36.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,lamenting the death of Dewey,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.24,0:30:38.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whom he recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.38,0:30:40.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as a person sympathetic to his cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.66,0:30:45.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It seemed a terrible irony that Dewey, who was
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.72,0:30:49.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,doing what he could to help the Vietnamese independence movement
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.06,0:30:53.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,should have been killed by the Vietnamese by a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.10,0:31:09.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,An elderly African-American woman answered the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.22,0:31:18.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I think she knew the instant she saw us why we were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.37,0:31:23.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the padre said, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.70,0:31:28.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"I'm... I'm terribly sorry to inform you,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.10,0:31:32.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but your son was killed in Vietnam."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.41,0:31:36.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And she just sat down. Didn't say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.34,0:31:42.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Then the... her husband says, "No, there's a mistake."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.34,0:31:44.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He comes back with this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.30,0:31:46.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And he said, "Look, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.54,0:31:50.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We got it yesterday, my... our son was still alive yesterday."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.92,0:31:54.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the chaplain looked at the letter
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.67,0:31:56.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and he said, "It's a week old.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.99,0:32:00.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I think your son was killed on the day he wrote this letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.06,0:32:11.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the fall of 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.52,0:32:13.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a week after Colonel Dewey's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.83,0:32:17.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,fresh French troops began arriving in Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.30,0:32:19.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,taking over from the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.64,0:32:23.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They quickly established control of the city
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.54,0:32:27.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and set out to reoccupy the entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.13,0:32:32.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh hoped somehow to achieve independence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.70,0:32:34.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,without a war with France,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.49,0:32:37.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and he still hoped the United States would intervene.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.07,0:32:39.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"You never had an empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.83,0:32:42.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,never exploited the Asian peoples,"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.38,0:32:44.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he would tell a visiting American journalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.25,0:32:49.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Do not be blinded by this issue of communism."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.10,0:32:54.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He did not want to fight the French as an enemy of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.03,0:33:01.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And, in fact, I saw the letters he wrote to President Truman
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.10,0:33:05.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,saying, "We believe in the same things you believe."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.46,0:33:08.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Those letters I saw in the CIA files,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.23,0:33:12.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,they had never been given to President Truman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.67,0:33:19.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In June of 1946,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.93,0:33:22.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh returned to Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.06,0:33:24.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a fruitless attempt to get the French
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.39,0:33:26.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to live up to a promise they had made
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.71,0:33:29.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of increased autonomy for his country.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.01,0:33:32.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,While Ho was away,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.37,0:33:34.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Giap began consolidating
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.77,0:33:37.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,communist control of the revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.24,0:33:40.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He conducted a merciless purge of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.35,0:33:43.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,members of rival nationalist parties
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.21,0:33:46.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and people he called "reactionary saboteurs"...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.76,0:33:49.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,landlords and moneylenders,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.88,0:33:52.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Trotskyites and Catholics,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.20,0:33:55.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,men and women accused of collaborating with the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.49,0:34:00.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Hundreds were shot, drowned, buried alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.13,0:34:16.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On December 19, 1946,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.86,0:34:19.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,after months of building tension,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.61,0:34:23.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,fighting broke out in Hanoi between the Viet Minh and the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.26,0:34:31.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Viet Minh proved no match for French firepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.11,0:34:41.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho, Giap, and their comrades slipped out of the city
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.44,0:34:45.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and returned to their mountain stronghold far to the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.44,0:34:50.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Those who have rifles will use their rifles,"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.72,0:34:52.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho declared in a radio address
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.95,0:34:55.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,calling for a nationwide guerrilla war.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.49,0:34:59.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Those who have swords will use swords;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.86,0:35:05.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,those who have no swords will use spades or sticks."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.06,0:35:38.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But the country Ho Chi Minh hoped to unite
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.17,0:35:40.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was itself bitterly divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.24,0:35:43.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Families were being torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.42,0:35:47.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Despite her father's position in the French government,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.77,0:35:52.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Duong Van Mai's sister felt compelled to answer Ho's call.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.64,0:35:59.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My older sister Thang was married to a man
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.08,0:36:02.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had great sympathy for the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.99,0:36:05.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And by that time Ho Chi Minh had evacuated
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.62,0:36:07.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,his government to the mountain base.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.72,0:36:10.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So my sister and her husband trekked
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.05,0:36:13.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,all the way from Hanoi toward the base
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.85,0:36:17.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in order to join the resistance against the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.78,0:36:22.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So the Vietnam War was really a civil war
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.38,0:36:24.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,down to the family level.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.46,0:36:35.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,France poured thousands of men into Vietnam...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.67,0:36:39.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French regulars, European mercenaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.55,0:36:44.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and colonial troops from Morocco, Algeria, Tunisia, and Senegal...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.08,0:36:48.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who fought alongside an army of Cambodians,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.68,0:36:49.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Laotians,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.75,0:36:52.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and anti-communist Vietnamese.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.61,0:36:58.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French forces managed to occupy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.73,0:37:02.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,most of the large towns and province capitals
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.38,0:37:06.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and established hundreds of isolated outposts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.73,0:37:12.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French also set out to try to win over rural Vietnamese
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.22,0:37:15.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,through a program they called pacification...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.79,0:37:17.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,pacification...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.45,0:37:20.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,building dikes, schools and roads,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.69,0:37:22.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and vaccinating children.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.66,0:37:28.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French would pacify a village
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.05,0:37:31.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and during the daytime they could control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.31,0:37:35.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But at night the Viet Minh would come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.20,0:37:38.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And so it was never completely secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.73,0:37:43.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My father would shake his head and said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.28,0:37:45.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Pacification is really futile
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.34,0:37:49.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because it's like trying to hold sand in your fingers."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.75,0:37:55.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Viet Minh mined roads,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.16,0:37:57.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,blew up bridges and railroads,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.06,0:38:00.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,ambushed French patrols,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.50,0:38:03.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and then disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.64,0:38:09.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French soldiers sometimes took revenge on the nearest village,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.75,0:38:12.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,burning homes, raping women,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.63,0:38:16.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,executing men suspected of aiding the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.37,0:38:57.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But the communists proved
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.35,0:39:00.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,every bit as ruthless as the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.40,0:39:03.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"It is better to kill even those who might be innocent,"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.96,0:39:08.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,one commander said, "than to let a guilty person go."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.80,0:39:11.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And they specifically targeted
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.84,0:39:14.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,anyone who had links to the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.07,0:39:17.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Once my father started working for the French,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.97,0:39:19.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,then he was a target,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.63,0:39:21.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,especially the higher he rose,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.76,0:39:23.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the bigger target he became.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.51,0:39:28.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A Viet Minh agent actually came in with a pistol
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.91,0:39:30.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to shoot him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.06,0:39:32.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but at the last moment decided not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.52,0:40:15.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French casualties continued to mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.85,0:40:19.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"There are days when we are so discouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.24,0:40:21.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that we would like to give it all up,"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.45,0:40:23.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a French soldier wrote his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.82,0:40:25.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Convoys under attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.80,0:40:27.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,roads cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.17,0:40:30.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,firing in all directions every night,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.47,0:40:32.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the indifference at home."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.33,0:40:45.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,While I was there I had the opportunity to call my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.64,0:40:50.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I was telling my mother what was happening over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.04,0:40:52.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and I was telling her how
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.07,0:40:56.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,she shouldn't believe what she sees in the newspaper and sees on television
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.29,0:40:57.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because we're losing the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.85,0:41:01.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I said, "And you'll probably never see me again
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.64,0:41:04.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because we're the most northern outpost
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.39,0:41:06.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the Marines have, you know."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.22,0:41:08.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We could literally... could look right into North Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.47,0:41:10.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We could see the sparks when the guns fired on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.88,0:41:13.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I said, "And everybody in my unit is dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.93,0:41:15.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I probably won't be coming back."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.41,0:41:17.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And my mother said, "No, you're coming back."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.68,0:41:21.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,She said, "I talk to God every day and you're special.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.60,0:41:23.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You're coming back."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.29,0:41:25.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I said, "Ma, everybody's mother
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.85,0:41:27.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,thinks that they're special.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.68,0:41:31.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You know, I'm putting pieces of special people in bags."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.92,0:41:39.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Truman's dramatic announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.65,0:41:41.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that Russia had the atom secret
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.12,0:41:44.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,caused state departments all over the world to stir uneasily.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.16,0:41:49.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were very aware that there was a Cold War
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.84,0:41:51.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and that we had an enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.62,0:41:54.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and that enemy was the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.72,0:41:58.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States stood at one pole
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.87,0:42:01.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the Soviet Union stood at the other pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.10,0:42:04.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was kind of a Manichean dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.12,0:42:06.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that there was evil and there was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.22,0:42:08.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And we were good, and the other side was evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.80,0:42:11.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It wasn't morally ambiguous.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.55,0:42:18.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Just a few weeks after Russia became a nuclear power,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.20,0:42:20.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,there was more stunning news...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.72,0:42:25.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,communist forces under Mao Zedong seized control of China.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.12,0:42:30.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Separate communist insurrections were also underway
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.62,0:42:34.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in the British colonies of Burma and Malaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.02,0:42:38.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In January 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.10,0:42:42.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Mao formally recognized Ho Chi Minh's insurgency
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.24,0:42:45.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and agreed to provide the arms, equipment,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.17,0:42:48.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and military training he had been seeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.68,0:42:51.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Soviets recognized the Viet Minh as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.00,0:42:54.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and also offered help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.40,0:42:57.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Truman, who was being blamed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.92,0:43:01.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,by his political opponents for having "lost" China,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.63,0:43:04.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and having failed to "contain" communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.47,0:43:07.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,approved a $23 million aid program
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.88,0:43:10.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for the French in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.28,0:43:14.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States was no longer neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.95,0:43:18.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were caught on the horns of a dilemma
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.80,0:43:23.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of how can we maintain our friendship and our alliance with the French
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.11,0:43:25.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and support them in Indochina
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.56,0:43:28.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,while we, as a former colony ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.80,0:43:31.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,sympathized with the Vietnamese and their aspirations
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.02,0:43:33.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for freedom and independence?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.46,0:43:41.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A highly trained and well-equipped North Korean Army
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.26,0:43:43.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,swarmed across the 38th parallel to attack
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.74,0:43:45.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,unprepared South Korean defenders.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.13,0:43:49.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In June of 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.45,0:43:52.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,China's ally, communist North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.67,0:43:54.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,invaded South Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.47,0:43:59.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Truman ordered tens of thousands of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.28,0:44:02.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American ground troops onto the Korean Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.99,0:44:11.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States and its allies
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.04,0:44:13.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,eventually pushed the invaders back north.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.80,0:44:17.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile in southern China,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.93,0:44:21.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Mao's military was beginning to turn the Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.39,0:44:23.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into a modern fighting force,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.35,0:44:29.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,capable of inflicting a heavy toll on the French occupiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.72,0:44:38.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In July, the Truman administration
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.14,0:44:40.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,quietly dispatched transport planes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.63,0:44:43.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and a shipload of jeeps to Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.01,0:44:46.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Thirty-five military advisors
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.60,0:44:48.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,went along to oversee their use.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.69,0:44:54.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,None of them, and no one in the American embassy,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.07,0:44:56.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,spoke a word of Vietnamese.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.79,0:45:02.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But the United States was now officially in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.43,0:45:06.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In October of 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.89,0:45:09.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hundreds of thousands of Chinese troops
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.85,0:45:12.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,began pouring into North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.27,0:45:15.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,driving the allies back down the peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.32,0:45:17.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As that fighting raged,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.94,0:45:21.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Truman continued to increase military aid
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.48,0:45:24.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for the French war in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.68,0:45:29.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If aggression is successful in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.94,0:45:33.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we can expect it to spread throughout Asia and Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.17,0:45:34.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and to this hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.57,0:45:39.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We are fighting in Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.31,0:45:41.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for our own national security and survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.47,0:45:50.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the autumn of 1951,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.05,0:45:53.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a young Massachusetts congressman
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.35,0:45:55.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,named John F. Kennedy
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.10,0:45:58.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dined at the rooftop bar of the Hotel Majestic
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.57,0:46:00.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,overlooking Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.28,0:46:03.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As he and his party ate,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.15,0:46:07.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,they could hear the thunder of guns across the Saigon River.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.54,0:46:10.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French commanders assured Kennedy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.00,0:46:13.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that with more American support,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.55,0:46:16.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French rule would be re-established.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.82,0:46:20.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Kennedy spent two hours with Seymour Topping,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.30,0:46:22.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a seasoned American reporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.51,0:46:25.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who gave him a very different perspective:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.86,0:46:28.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the French were losing, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.07,0:46:31.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and many Vietnamese, who had once admired the Americans,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.97,0:46:35.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were beginning to despise them for backing the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.94,0:46:39.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Kennedy believed the reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.49,0:46:42.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Unless the United States could persuade the Vietnamese
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.98,0:46:46.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that it was as opposed to "injustice and inequality"
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.67,0:46:48.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as it was to communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.33,0:46:51.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he told his constituents when he got home,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.49,0:46:55.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the current effort would result in "foredoomed failure."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.57,0:47:07.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In 1952,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.15,0:47:10.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Dwight Eisenhower was elected president,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.37,0:47:12.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in part because he promised
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.06,0:47:14.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to take a tougher stance on communism.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.61,0:47:18.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That year, American taxpayers
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.98,0:47:21.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were footing more than 30% of the bill
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.82,0:47:24.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for the French war in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.98,0:47:26.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Within two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.58,0:47:29.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that number would rise to nearly 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.14,0:47:35.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And many of you ask this question:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.40,0:47:40.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Why is the United States spending hundreds of millions of dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.63,0:47:44.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,supporting the forces of the French Union
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.48,0:47:47.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in the fight against communism in Indochina?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.30,0:47:50.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I think perhaps if we go over to the map here,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.54,0:47:53.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I can indicate to you why it is so vitally important.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.43,0:47:55.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Here's Indochina.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.71,0:47:58.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If Indochina falls,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.48,0:48:01.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Thailand is put in almost impossible position.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.11,0:48:04.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The same is true of Malaya with its rubber and tin.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.81,0:48:09.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Now may I say that as far as the war in Indochina is concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.12,0:48:14.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that I was there, right on the battlefield, or close to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.13,0:48:17.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and it's a bloody war, and it's a bitter one.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.78,0:48:27.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By 1953, the French had been fighting for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.62,0:48:30.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They had suffered over 100,000 casualties
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.96,0:48:33.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and failed to pacify the countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.13,0:48:37.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Six commanders had come and gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.95,0:48:40.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the seventh commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.20,0:48:43.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Henri Navarre, assured his countrymen
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.40,0:48:45.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that victory was near.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.59,0:48:48.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Now we can see it clearly," he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.28,0:48:51.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"like the light at the end of the tunnel."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.85,0:48:57.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, large parts of the French population
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.21,0:49:00.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were horrified by reports of French brutality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.41,0:49:03.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the widespread use of napalm...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.99,0:49:05.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,gelatinized petroleum
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.12,0:49:07.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that burned foliage,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.81,0:49:08.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.99,0:49:10.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and human flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.52,0:49:17.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,When returning French troops disembarked at Marseilles,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.02,0:49:21.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,members of the longshoremen's union pelted them with rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.88,0:49:24.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Parisian leftists began to call the conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.88,0:49:27.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"La Sale Guerre"... "The Dirty War."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.41,0:49:38.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The camera was a close-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.84,0:49:41.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was over the shoulder of this storm trooper
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.89,0:49:44.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had a kid by the scruff of his shirt and
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.39,0:49:45.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he smacks him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.81,0:49:46.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,People screaming...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.21,0:49:48.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,At that moment in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.54,0:49:51.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I realized that anybody who really cared for America
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.68,0:49:53.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was sent halfway around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.38,0:49:55.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,chasing some ghost in a jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.12,0:49:59.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, my country's being torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.86,0:50:02.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So I saw somebody who looked like my dad
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.32,0:50:04.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hitting somebody who looked like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.64,0:50:06.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Whose side would I be on?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.99,0:50:16.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In Korea, three years of combat end
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.24,0:50:20.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as United Nations and communist negotiators at Panmunjom sign a truce.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.56,0:50:22.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In July of 1953,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.17,0:50:26.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Korean War ended in a negotiated settlement
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.74,0:50:28.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and a still-divided peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.59,0:50:32.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American policymakers saw it as proof
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.43,0:50:35.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that communism in Asia could be contained.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.49,0:50:40.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That fall, the French indicated their willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.78,0:50:44.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to begin talks to end the fighting in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.66,0:50:47.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh agreed to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.69,0:50:52.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But before the negotiators were to convene in Geneva,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.81,0:50:57.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,each side sought to improve its position on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.86,0:51:01.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Navarre set up a fortified base
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.70,0:51:04.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a remote valley in northwestern Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.74,0:51:06.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,called Dien Bien Phu,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.71,0:51:09.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where he hoped to lure the Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.22,0:51:11.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into a decisive battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.16,0:51:17.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Navarre was certain that superior French firepower and air support
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.69,0:51:21.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,would crush any attack by the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.69,0:51:24.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He and his commanders saw no need to worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.64,0:51:29.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the jungle-covered hills that overlooked his 11,000 men,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.16,0:51:31.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dug in on the valley floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.94,0:51:36.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The artillery commander was so confident of victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.53,0:51:40.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he complained, "I have more guns than I need."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.11,0:51:45.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Giap saw his chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.33,0:51:49.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"We decided to wipe out at all costs
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.62,0:51:53.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the whole enemy force at Dien Bien Phu," he remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:51:58.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To do it, he pulled off one of the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.23,0:52:01.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,logistical feats in military history...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.18,0:52:04.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a feat that would be restaged in propaganda films
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.84,0:52:07.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and celebrated for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.69,0:52:11.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A quarter of a million civilian porters...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.69,0:52:13.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,nearly half of them women...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.40,0:52:16.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,moved everything he needed for a siege,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.64,0:52:18.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from sacks of rice
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.42,0:52:20.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to disassembled artillery pieces,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.98,0:52:23.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on foot through the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.95,0:52:28.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Giap surrounded the valley with 50,000 soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.77,0:52:31.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and 200 big guns,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.04,0:52:34.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dug-in and camouflaged so well
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.08,0:52:36.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,they could not be spotted from the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.36,0:52:44.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On March 13, 1954,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.16,0:52:46.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Viet Minh artillery on the hillsides
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.89,0:52:49.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,began raining down 50 shells a minute
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.85,0:52:52.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on the French troops huddled below.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.00,0:52:57.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The airstrip was destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.06,0:53:03.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The besieged troops could only be reinforced
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.15,0:53:05.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and resupplied by airdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.66,0:53:13.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French artillery commander, who had underestimated his enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.74,0:53:15.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.36,0:53:19.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The airlift to Dien Bien Phu continues...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.63,0:53:21.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,vital men and supplies for the heroic garrison
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.01,0:53:25.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that has defied the massed Viet Minh onslaughts for over six weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.41,0:53:28.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Today, Dien Bien Phu is a human dam
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.10,0:53:29.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,trying to stem the red tide
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.75,0:53:32.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that threatens to engulf Southeast Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.66,0:53:35.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French government begged
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.31,0:53:37.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Eisenhower to intervene.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.30,0:53:39.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He refused to act
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.67,0:53:44.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,without Congressional approval and support from European allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.57,0:53:46.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Britain said no
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.87,0:53:50.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the Congress would not support unilateral action.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.16,0:53:53.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The communists under Ho Chi Minh are able to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.43,0:53:55.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,claim that they are fighting for independence
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.68,0:53:58.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the French appear to be fighting for a maintain...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.19,0:53:59.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,maintenance of colonial rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.90,0:54:01.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I therefore believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.29,0:54:04.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,before the United States moves in, in any degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.44,0:54:06.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that independence must be granted to the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.96,0:54:09.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the people must support the struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.18,0:54:14.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"I am convinced," Eisenhower confided to his diary,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.39,0:54:18.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"that no military victory is possible in this theater."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.19,0:54:21.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Still, without consulting Congress,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.96,0:54:26.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the president had secretly sent more American transport planes,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.24,0:54:31.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,their markings painted over and flown by civilian contractors,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.69,0:54:36.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to help resupply the desperate French troops at Dien Bien Phu.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.97,0:54:42.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Everyone understood that in and of itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.60,0:54:45.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam didn't mean very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.24,0:54:48.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But they believed, I believed,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.96,0:54:50.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,if we lost it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.47,0:54:53.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the rest of Asia would tumble to communism.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.21,0:54:58.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have broader considerations that might follow
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.17,0:55:02.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,what you would call the falling domino principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.22,0:55:05.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have a row of dominoes set up,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.68,0:55:08.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and you knock over the first one,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.70,0:55:11.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and what will happen to the last one is the certainty
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.20,0:55:13.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that it will go over very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.30,0:55:39.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On the afternoon of May 7, 1954,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.02,0:55:41.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,after 55 days of siege,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.85,0:55:46.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the exhausted French forces at Dien Bien Phu surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.02,0:55:54.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They had lost 8,000 men, killed, wounded, or missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.06,0:56:01.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Giap had lost three times as many,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.72,0:56:04.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but he had won a great victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.60,0:56:26.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Even Duong Van Mai's parents could not help but be impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.69,0:56:30.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were very proud that the Viet Minh had defeated
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.95,0:56:34.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the French, this great Western power.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.05,0:56:37.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Admiration and respect on the one hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.89,0:56:40.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but fear on the other hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.21,0:56:42.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And fear was the stronger emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.49,0:56:47.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"We have been caught bluffing by our enemies,"
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.25,0:56:50.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Senate Minority Leader Lyndon Johnson said.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.86,0:56:56.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Today it is Indochina, tomorrow Asia may be in flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.08,0:57:01.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the day after, the Western Alliance will lie in ruins."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.35,0:57:04.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We should have seen it as the end of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.30,0:57:06.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the colonial era in Southeast Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.64,0:57:07.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,which it really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.62,0:57:11.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But instead we saw it in Cold War terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.37,0:57:15.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and we saw it as a defeat for the free world
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.47,0:57:17.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that was related to the rise of China.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.41,0:57:22.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was a total misreading of a pivotal event,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.55,0:57:25.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,which cost us very dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.12,0:57:34.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The former home of the League of Nations, Geneva, Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.12,0:57:37.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where East is meeting West in the international conference
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.10,0:57:40.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that may decisively affect the political future of Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.05,0:57:44.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The day after the fall of Dien Bien Phu,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.13,0:57:47.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,diplomats from nine nations gathered in Geneva
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.58,0:57:49.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to settle the future of Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.51,0:57:55.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The talks dragged on for nearly two-and-a-half months.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.07,0:57:59.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Despite their victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.58,0:58:03.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh and General Giap could not keep fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.28,0:58:07.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,without more support from China and the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.51,0:58:12.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But China had lost a million men in Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.17,0:58:15.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and did not want to become involved in another war
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.23,0:58:16.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,along its border.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.62,0:58:22.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Soviet Union was hoping to ease tensions with the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.46,0:58:26.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Both of Ho Chi Minh's communist patrons
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.19,0:58:29.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,urged him to agree to a negotiated settlement,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.65,0:58:33.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a partition like the one that had ended the Korean War.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.79,0:58:37.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho had no option but to give in.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.25,0:58:44.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the end, no one was satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.14,0:58:50.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam was temporarily to be divided at the 17th parallel.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.13,0:58:55.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The 130,000 French-led troops stationed in the North
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.80,0:58:57.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were to withdraw to the South,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.99,0:59:02.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and somewhere between 50,000 and 90,000 Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.06,0:59:04.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were to "re-group" to the North.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.97,0:59:08.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The two halves would be separated by a demilitarized zone
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.98,0:59:11.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,until an election could be held
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.04,0:59:14.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to reunify North and South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.92,0:59:19.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,an election everyone knew Ho Chi Minh would win.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.34,0:59:55.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We had started walking up
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.70,0:59:58.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and we had probably gotten about a third of the way up the hill
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.15,0:59:59.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and then they unleashed on us.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.66,1:00:04.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were in the middle of this horrible shit sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.25,1:00:06.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That's what we called it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.61,1:00:15.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,One of the things that I learned in the war is that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.74,1:00:17.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we're not the top species on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.90,1:00:19.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because we're nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.52,1:00:25.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,People talk a lot about how well the military turns, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.56,1:00:28.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,kids into, you know, killing machines and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.22,1:00:30.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I'll always argue that it's just finishing school.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.72,1:00:40.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Braving the dangers
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.99,1:00:43.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of the open sea in tiny, rickety craft,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.41,1:00:45.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,thousands of Roman Catholic and Buddhist faith
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.87,1:00:48.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,have found life impossible under the communists.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.35,1:00:50.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For them, it's freedom or nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.77,1:00:56.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Under the Geneva Accords,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.74,1:00:59.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,civilians living in either half of Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.99,1:01:02.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who wanted to relocate to the other
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.32,1:01:04.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,would have 300 days to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.35,1:01:09.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My mother and father wanted to stay
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.15,1:01:11.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and meet my sister Thang again
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.52,1:01:13.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because they knew Thang would come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.63,1:01:16.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But on the other hand they couldn't risk that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.15,1:01:19.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were convinced that when Ho Chi Minh
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.97,1:01:22.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and his government arrived in Hanoi,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.59,1:01:26.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,my father would be the first one to be killed
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.39,1:01:28.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and all of us would be persecuted.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.41,1:01:33.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I remember the day we left.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.61,1:01:37.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I looked around and I thought, "I never come back here again."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.12,1:01:41.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was extremely traumatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.07,1:01:46.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was like the ground was suddenly cut from under you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.36,1:01:51.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the end, some 900,000 refugees,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.29,1:01:55.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including more than half of all the Catholics living in the North,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.45,1:01:57.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,fled to the South,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.62,1:02:00.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,many of them aboard American ships.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.56,1:02:08.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States hoped somehow to encourage the building
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.23,1:02:10.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of a legitimate government in the South.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.66,1:02:17.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That government was now headed by Ngo Dinh Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.69,1:02:20.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Both a Roman Catholic and a Confucian
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.27,1:02:22.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a largely Buddhist country,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.47,1:02:24.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he was a celibate bachelor
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.38,1:02:27.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had once planned to be a priest.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.52,1:02:33.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The war for us really started when we became the partner,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.01,1:02:38.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,or I would say the victim, of President Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.10,1:02:44.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were going to help him turn South Vietnam into a democracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.37,1:02:45.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That's what he said he wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.85,1:02:46.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And we believed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.70,1:02:49.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Like Ho Chi Minh,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.15,1:02:52.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem had spent years abroad seeking support
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.86,1:02:56.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for his own brand of Vietnamese nationalism.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.54,1:02:58.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He was a veteran politician
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.45,1:03:00.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whose loathing for the French
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.88,1:03:03.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was matched only by his hatred for the communists,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.74,1:03:05.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had imprisoned him
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.30,1:03:09.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and buried alive his eldest brother and his nephew.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.03,1:03:13.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem was aloof, autocratic,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.56,1:03:17.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,mistrustful of anyone much beyond his own family.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.59,1:03:20.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He also proved to be shrewd, resourceful,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.96,1:03:25.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and skilled at exploiting the weaknesses of his opponents.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.00,1:03:30.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But he faced a daunting task in creating a new country.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.22,1:03:35.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French, who still had thousands of troops
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.80,1:03:37.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,detested Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.35,1:03:41.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Several provinces were under the sway of religious sects
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.89,1:03:43.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with armies of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.49,1:03:48.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Tens of thousands of Viet Minh soldiers had gone north,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.48,1:03:50.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but several thousand cadre...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.59,1:03:53.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,trained and dedicated Communist Party workers...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.01,1:03:58.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,had stayed behind to organize resistance in the countryside.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.08,1:04:04.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And Saigon itself was ruled by the Binh Xuyen,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.21,1:04:07.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a crime syndicate backed by the French.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.70,1:04:10.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the French were behind the Binh Xuyen,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.20,1:04:11.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,sort of supporting them
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.91,1:04:14.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because they didn't want Diem to succeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.64,1:04:17.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And that became the central contest.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.55,1:04:20.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Some in the CIA believed that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.98,1:04:24.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem could be the savior of South Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.67,1:04:26.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Others were not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.75,1:04:28.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"He is a messiah without a message,"
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.99,1:04:31.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,one diplomat reported to Washington.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.77,1:04:35.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The U.S. ambassador agreed.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.75,1:04:39.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On April 27, 1955,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.15,1:04:41.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Eisenhower decided to end
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.92,1:04:45.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American support for Diem's regime.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.38,1:04:50.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But then Diem made an all-out assault
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.61,1:04:52.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on the Binh Xuyen syndicate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.36,1:04:57.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Suddenly in the middle of the day
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.19,1:05:01.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we heard gunfire and then we saw flames
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.34,1:05:04.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the neighborhood was burning.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.23,1:05:06.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There are hundreds of dead and wounded on both sides
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.83,1:05:09.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as the street fighting continues for an entire week.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.95,1:05:11.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For the United States,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.01,1:05:13.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the situation presents a grave problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.07,1:05:18.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem finally regains control of Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.58,1:05:22.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the end, Diem's forces prevailed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.63,1:05:27.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Eisenhower now saw no option
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.46,1:05:29.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but to stick with Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.80,1:05:33.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French then announced their intention
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.67,1:05:37.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to withdraw completely from South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.24,1:05:40.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,ending nearly a century of occupation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.32,1:05:44.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem became wildly popular
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.73,1:05:49.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because he seemed to embody the nationalist cause in the South.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.92,1:05:51.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He succeeded in getting the French
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.79,1:05:53.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,out of Vietnam all the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.86,1:05:57.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And Ho Chi Minh had only got them out of the northern half.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.00,1:05:59.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Flush with victory,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.41,1:06:02.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem called for a referendum in the South.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.29,1:06:08.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The CIA warned him not to meddle too much with the returns.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.65,1:06:11.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But when the ballots were counted,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.64,1:06:16.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem claimed to have won 98.2% of the vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.94,1:06:22.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On October 26, 1955,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.59,1:06:26.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ngo Dinh Diem named himself the first president
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.03,1:06:29.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of the brand-new Republic of Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.05,1:06:36.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The election to reunify the North and South that had been promised at Geneva
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.13,1:06:37.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,would never be held.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.67,1:06:42.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He became our ally,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.06,1:06:44.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,or rather our master,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.29,1:06:47.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because the goal of preventing the communists
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.71,1:06:50.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from taking over the South was so strong
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.20,1:06:54.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that we couldn't afford for him to lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.11,1:06:58.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So Diem started to boss us around.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.47,1:07:00.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And this was a typical relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.74,1:07:03.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You need any ally you believe
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.12,1:07:06.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to be the centerpiece of your foreign policy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.08,1:07:07.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They understand that right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.19,1:07:10.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the tail wags the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.49,1:07:17.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,From the Far East comes a distinguished visitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.16,1:07:19.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Ngo Dinh Diem of Vietnam is accorded
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.75,1:07:22.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,one of President Eisenhower's rare airport greetings,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.93,1:07:25.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as he arrives for a four-day state visit.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.60,1:07:29.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Diem, one of America's staunchest allies in Southeast Asia,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.43,1:07:32.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,will seek an increase in aid to shore up his country
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.07,1:07:34.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,against increasing communist pressure,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.02,1:07:37.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a request to which the president lends a sympathetic ear.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.46,1:07:43.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Most politicians, Democrats as well as Republicans,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.38,1:07:45.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,now seemed to share the changing views
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.62,1:07:47.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of Senator John F. Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.09,1:07:51.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,South Vietnam is "our offspring," he said.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.14,1:07:53.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"We cannot abandon it."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.11,1:07:57.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If it fell, the United States would be "held responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.22,1:08:01.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and our prestige in Asia will sink to a new low."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.92,1:08:06.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There had never before been a South Vietnamese nation,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.82,1:08:09.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but Americans, who had rebuilt much of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.55,1:08:11.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,their own country during the New Deal
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.00,1:08:14.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and had helped rebuild Western Europe
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.20,1:08:15.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,through the Marshall Plan,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.09,1:08:20.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were convinced they could build one nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.83,1:08:24.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Eisenhower ordered scores of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.98,1:08:27.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American civilians to South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.77,1:08:30.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,full of plans for economic development
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.58,1:08:35.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,meant to win, he hoped, the hearts and minds of the Vietnamese people.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.51,1:08:40.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But those civilians would always
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.71,1:08:43.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,be outnumbered by military advisors,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.48,1:08:48.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with orders to modernize, train, and equip Diem's forces,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.23,1:08:52.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,now called the Army of the Republic of Vietnam...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.44,1:08:53.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the ARVN.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.06,1:08:58.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Some ARVN officers found American methods
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.46,1:09:04.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,unsuited to the guerrilla war they expected to wage against the communists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.22,1:09:06.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Most American military advisors
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.55,1:09:08.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were veterans of the war in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.12,1:09:12.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,determined to prepare South Vietnamese forces
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.47,1:09:16.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to slow a conventional invasion from the North.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.53,1:09:21.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But no one in North Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.77,1:09:24.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was planning a conventional invasion.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.69,1:09:29.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was focused on rebuilding his country,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.48,1:09:32.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,devastated by more than a decade of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.04,1:09:39.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The communists imposed brutal land reforms
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.36,1:09:41.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,modeled on those underway in China
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.79,1:09:45.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with a ruthlessness that left thousands of people dead,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.91,1:09:49.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including not only landlords who had sided with the French,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.97,1:09:53.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but also many villagers who had fought with the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.55,1:10:00.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was still determined to reunite Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.39,1:10:04.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But he worried that if he took direct military action against the South,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.69,1:10:08.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the United States would be drawn more deeply into the struggle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.18,1:10:11.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He cautioned his comrades in the South to
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.57,1:10:14.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,put their faith in political agitation
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.37,1:10:16.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and avoid violence.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.20,1:10:21.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But that message rang hollow among
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.51,1:10:24.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,embattled Southern revolutionaries struggling
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.49,1:10:28.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to survive under Diem's increasingly harsh regime.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.39,1:10:34.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In a campaign he called "Denounce the Communists,"
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.00,1:10:39.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem had imprisoned tens of thousands of citizens without trial
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.05,1:10:43.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and ordered the executions of hundreds more.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.06,1:10:48.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Now, the communists took matters into their own hands
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.88,1:10:52.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and began attacking South Vietnamese officials.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.11,1:11:36.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As violence in South Vietnam intensified,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.45,1:11:39.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,new leaders emerged in Hanoi.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.78,1:11:43.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh would remain the face of the revolution around the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.50,1:11:46.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but he now began to share power
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.68,1:11:50.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with men who were growing impatient with his caution,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.84,1:11:54.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,men about whom Americans knew almost nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.58,1:11:59.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The most important proved to be a carpenter's son
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.71,1:12:04.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from Quang Tri province in the South named Le Duan.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.62,1:12:09.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He had helped found the Indochinese Communist Party,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.36,1:12:12.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,survived nearly ten years in a French prison,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.59,1:12:15.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and proved himself a shrewd political infighter
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.91,1:12:19.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as he rose to become First Secretary of the party.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.10,1:12:55.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By 1959,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.87,1:12:58.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Le Duan and his hardline allies
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.51,1:13:02.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were gaining influence within the North Vietnamese Politburo
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.42,1:13:04.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and beginning to change its policy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.19,1:13:10.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They now argued that Hanoi should do everything within its power
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.36,1:13:14.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to help Southern revolutionaries remove Diem by force.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.14,1:13:39.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Now, bands of 40 to 50 armed Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.94,1:13:43.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,began slipping back home into South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.48,1:13:47.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,following jungle paths hacked through the Laotian mountains
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.44,1:13:51.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the Americans would soon call the Ho Chi Minh Trail.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.21,1:14:00.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Violence against the Diem regime steadily accelerated.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.85,1:14:14.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On the evening of July 8, 1959,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.48,1:14:15.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,at Bien Hoa,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.85,1:14:18.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,20 miles northeast of Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.46,1:14:21.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,six American military advisors
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.12,1:14:23.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were watching a movie in their mess hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.05,1:14:29.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Viet Minh guerrillas, who had crept silently into the compound,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.09,1:14:31.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,opened fire through the windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.60,1:14:39.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Major Dale Buis from Pender, Nebraska,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.65,1:14:44.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and Master Sergeant Chester Ovnand from Copperas Cove, Texas,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.37,1:14:45.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.51,1:14:49.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were the first American soldiers
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.94,1:14:53.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to die from enemy fire in the Vietnam War.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.52,1:15:00.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We must prove all over again, to a watching world,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.22,1:15:03.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as we sit on a most conspicuous stage,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.77,1:15:07.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whether this nation, conceived as it is
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.79,1:15:14.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with its freedom of choice, its breadth of opportunity, its range of alternatives,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.51,1:15:18.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,can compete with the single-minded advance of the communist system.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.67,1:15:22.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On November 8, 1960,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.31,1:15:27.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,John Fitzgerald Kennedy was elected president of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.14,1:15:30.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,His vice president was Senator Lyndon Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.57,1:15:35.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They had narrowly beaten Vice President Richard Nixon
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.04,1:15:38.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and his running mate, Senator Henry Cabot Lodge.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.98,1:15:43.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,During the campaign, both Kennedy and Nixon had
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.12,1:15:47.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,pledged to hold the line against international communism
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.31,1:15:49.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,wherever it seemed to be a threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.82,1:15:54.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But very few Americans knew or cared about
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.18,1:15:57.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,what was going on in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.40,1:16:00.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Six weeks after Kennedy's election,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.89,1:16:03.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,at a remote jungle village called Tan Lap
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.62,1:16:05.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,near the Cambodian border,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.90,1:16:09.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,representatives of southern revolutionary groups
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.09,1:16:13.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,met to form a new organization to replace the Viet Minh,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.48,1:16:16.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dedicated to overthrowing Ngo Dinh Diem
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.66,1:16:19.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and ousting the foreigners supporting him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.29,1:16:26.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Behind the scenes, Le Duan and his communist comrades in Hanoi
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.18,1:16:28.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were orchestrating everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.36,1:16:32.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The new organization would be called
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.65,1:16:34.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the National Liberation Front...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.23,1:16:36.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the NLF.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.57,1:16:41.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The armed wing of the NLF was called
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.09,1:16:43.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the People's Liberation Armed Forces,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.92,1:16:47.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but its enemies in Saigon and Washington preferred
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.46,1:16:49.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a more disparaging term.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.41,1:16:53.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In their eyes, the revolutionaries were
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.06,1:16:56.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Communist Traitors to the Vietnamese Nation...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.56,1:16:59.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Viet Cong.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.49,1:17:50.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Let every nation know,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.93,1:17:55.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whether it wishes us well or ill,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.19,1:17:59.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that we shall pay any price,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.09,1:18:02.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,bear any burden,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.25,1:18:05.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,meet any hardship,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.77,1:18:08.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,support any friend,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.10,1:18:10.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,oppose any foe,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.93,1:18:14.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to assure the survival and the success of liberty.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.27,1:18:29.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For me, I'd always thought of courage
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.22,1:18:31.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as charging enemy bunkers
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.30,1:18:33.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,or standing up under fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.35,1:18:36.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But just to walk,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.20,1:18:39.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,day after day from village to village
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.82,1:18:43.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and through the paddies and up into the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.77,1:18:48.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,just to get up in the morning and look out at the land
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.72,1:18:52.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and think, "In a few minutes I'll be walking out there
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.26,1:18:55.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and will my corpse be there, over there?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.80,1:18:57.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Will I lose a leg out there?"
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.55,1:19:02.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Just to walk felt incredibly brave.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.76,1:19:05.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I would sometimes look at my legs as I walked,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.47,1:19:07.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,thinking, how am I doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.67,0:00:56.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从越南回到国内
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.77,0:01:00.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,就跟在越南打仗一样难受
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.67,0:01:04.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,许多年来 没有人谈论越南的事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.33,0:01:09.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们有一对年轻的夫妇朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.03,0:01:14.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但认识12年后 双方妻子才在交谈中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.23,0:01:17.24,中文对白,,0,0,0,,发现我们两位丈夫都曾在越南当过陆战队员
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.62,0:01:19.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从来就没说到这事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.96,0:01:21.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从来都不提及这事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.99,0:01:24.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而整个国家就都像是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.35,0:01:27.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,真是太分裂扭曲了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.14,0:01:32.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这就像是住在一个有酒鬼老爸的家里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.04,0:01:36.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"嘘 我们不能说这个"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.26,0:01:40.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们国家就是这样对待越战的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.06,0:01:42.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我想是直到最近不久
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.94,0:01:45.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,婴儿潮那一代的人终于开始问道
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.62,0:01:47.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.62,0:01:49.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,究竟发生了什么"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.10,0:02:00.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在我们国家所需要的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:02.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,就是愈合创伤
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.88,0:02:05.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并把越南抛到身后
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.14,0:02:20.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这场悲剧性战争里的杀戮必须停止了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.45,0:02:33.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,威斯特摩兰将军的策略
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.52,0:02:35.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,正在产生效果了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:39.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,敌人不再更接近于胜利了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:48.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不管你们是怎么看的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.49,0:02:52.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们此时的境况比预期的要乐观得多
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.66,0:02:59.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,你没有很坦诚地说明
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.66,0:03:03.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们在多大程度上介入了越南
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:05.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们增派了援助
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.64,0:03:07.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,给那边的政府及其后勤
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:09.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们没有派作战部队去那里
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:13.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在有着一连串的多米诺骨牌
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.45,0:03:16.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,你推倒了第一块和最后一块牌
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:17.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那么它肯定会倾倒
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.59,0:03:19.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,如果他们成功入侵了韩国
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.73,0:03:22.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那我们就等着赤潮传遍亚洲和欧洲
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.95,0:03:24.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,传到我们这个半球吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:04:03.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,维克多·弗兰克从二战的集中营里幸存了下来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.22,0:04:05.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他写了本书叫《活出意义来》
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:10.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说 "人活着就是一种折磨
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.46,0:04:14.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,人要活下来则是要在这种痛苦里找到生存的意义"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:19.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对于我们这些深受越战折磨的人
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.11,0:04:24.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这句话便成了我们的追求
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.83,0:04:41.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国一开始是秘密介入越南事务的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.37,0:04:47.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并在30年后以失败告终
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.02,0:04:49.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,且整个世界有目共睹
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.32,0:04:56.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这一切都始于光鲜体面的人们
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.59,0:04:59.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,满怀真心 却又严重误解
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.25,0:05:03.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及美国的过度自信和冷战误判
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.84,0:05:06.26,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而它如此拖延
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.26,0:05:09.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,则是因为蒙混过关似乎要好过
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:12.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,承认它是始于两大政党的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.11,0:05:15.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,5位美国总统的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:18.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,悲剧性决定
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.68,0:05:22.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在越战结束前
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.32,0:05:26.07,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有5.8万多美国人死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.96,0:05:30.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,至少25万南越军队
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:33.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也死于这场冲突
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:37.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有100万的北越士兵和越共游击队员
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:39.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也死于其中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:47.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,南北共有200万平民
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.81,0:05:49.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,可能也灰飞烟灭了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.50,0:05:51.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有邻国老挝和柬埔寨的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:55.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,成千上万人也都就此消亡
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:05:59.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对许多越南人来说
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.36,0:06:01.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这是一场残酷的内战
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:05.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对其他人而言 这是百年独立斗争中的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.29,0:06:08.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,血腥高潮篇章
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.28,0:06:16.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对于出国参战的美国人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:19.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及国内反战的美国人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:23.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有那些只在夜间新闻瞥上一眼的人们
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.80,0:06:27.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越战是一场十年的痛苦挣扎
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:31.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也是自内战后最为分裂的时期
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.81,0:06:37.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南似乎使得一切都陷入了质疑中
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.65,0:06:41.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,荣誉与勇气的价值
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.03,0:06:45.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,残暴与仁慈的品质
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.83,0:06:50.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国政府的坦诚
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.65,0:06:55.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及爱国者的真正含义
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.03,0:07:03.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,历经了这事的人们
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.95,0:07:06.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一直都无法将之忘怀
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.77,0:07:09.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一直都未停止争辩究竟发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.33,0:07:13.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,为什么一切会变得如此严重错误
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.33,0:07:14.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,谁该为此担责
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:18.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这一切是否值得
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.77,0:08:58.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国队印度支那的征服始于
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.73,0:09:03.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1858年对越南古老港口岘港的攻占
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.93,0:09:08.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国用了50年才占有了这整个地区
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.60,0:09:10.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有老挝 有柬埔寨
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.28,0:09:13.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有一片1200英里长的区域
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.54,0:09:16.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这就是后来所称的越南
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.37,0:09:22.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这整个地区都由法国总督所统治
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:24.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而他的宫殿就在河内
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.07,0:09:29.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国人在很大程度上靠种植园过活
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:32.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而像西贡之类的城市
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:35.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也尽量造得像法国的一样
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:40.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们多数人甚至都不用去学
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.61,0:09:42.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,自己臣民所讲的语言
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.34,0:09:46.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,相反他们扶植了一系列的傀儡皇帝
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:51.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并网罗了一堆讲法语的越南人官员
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.12,0:09:52.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,当然这些官吏们
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.21,0:09:54.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,得愿意为法国人进行统治
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.40,0:09:59.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国人利用民众来干活
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.98,0:10:02.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,建造道路 运河
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:04.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,铁路和桥梁
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.70,0:10:25.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南人民对于法国人的占领可没服服帖帖的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.17,0:10:29.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,毕竟他们之前就已经抵抗过中国人的入侵了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.89,0:10:34.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,到20世纪早期 民族主义风头正盛
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:37.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但是任何胆敢抵抗殖民统治的人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.71,0:10:41.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都会面临着流亡 入狱 甚至砍头
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.86,0:11:38.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我对他们的痛恨是纯粹的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.62,0:11:40.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,纯粹的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:42.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我是那么地痛恨他们
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.44,0:11:45.70,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我也那么地害怕他们
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.88,0:11:52.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我实在是被他们吓坏了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.81,0:12:03.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我越怕他们 我就越恨他们
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.52,0:12:09.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我那时是个18岁的陆战队步枪兵
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.23,0:12:11.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我的高中毕业证上的墨水都还没干呢
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:14.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我不想在队友面前丢脸
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.74,0:12:18.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但我实在是很害怕
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.97,0:12:21.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我觉得自己在那里的全部时候都是为了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.88,0:12:23.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,保住自己的荣誉
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:40.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在1919年春天
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:43.81,中文对白,,0,0,0,,战胜的协约国各方汇聚巴黎
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:47.00,中文对白,,0,0,0,,重建一战后的残破世界
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:51.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国总统伍德罗·威尔逊率领代表团
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:53.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,入驻柯立龙酒店
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:13:00.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,某天 有名高高瘦瘦的29岁男子
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.24,0:13:02.81,中文对白,,0,0,0,,带着一份请愿书前来交给总统
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:06.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他和一些越南民族主义者写了这份请愿
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.86,0:13:10.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,威尔逊的声明鼓舞了他
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.30,0:13:13.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,总统说殖民地人民的利益应该得到
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.45,0:13:16.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,与欧洲统治者同等分量的重视
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.03,0:13:21.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这男子请求将此原则应用于他的祖国
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.03,0:13:26.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,总统秘书承诺说会转交给威尔逊看的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.79,0:13:29.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但没有证据表明他兑现了这一承诺
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:33.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那名男子叫做 阮必成
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.05,0:13:37.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不过这时他用的是化名 阮爱国
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.67,0:13:39.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,爱国者的意思
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.16,0:13:43.24,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在他漫长而神秘的生涯里
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.26,0:13:46.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他共用过约70个不同的化名
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.19,0:13:50.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最后固定用了个 "最具启发性的"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.45,0:13:52.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.49,0:13:56.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明这个人
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:13:59.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他成功地给自己营造了一个形象
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.79,0:14:05.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他完全献身于将自己的国家和人民
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:07.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从外国统治中解放出来
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:12.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,甚至还牺牲了自己的个人幸福和生活
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.99,0:14:15.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他没有自己的家庭
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.15,0:14:19.70,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在越南人看来  这是很大的牺牲
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:23.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为我们每个人都需要有个家庭
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:26.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明生于1890年
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.99,0:14:30.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他是法国政权里的一名小官的儿子
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.04,0:14:34.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为参加示威反对傀儡皇帝
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:37.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,及其背后的法国势力
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.47,0:14:41.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明被学校开除并成为逃犯
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.85,0:14:48.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他于1911年离开越南并流亡了30年
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.13,0:14:53.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他登上一艘法国邮轮并当上了帮厨
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:14:56.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还到过纽约和波士顿
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.14,0:15:00.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并在这里的帕克豪斯酒店当了一段时间的糕点师傅
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.36,0:15:03.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他在伦敦铲过雪
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.20,0:15:06.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在巴黎洗印过照片
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:11.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明在那里加入了法国社会党
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.08,0:15:15.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不过在发现了列宁的反殖民论述后
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:17.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他就成为了一名共产主义者
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.94,0:15:21.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他被邀请到莫斯科进行学习
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:24.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并接受训练成为了苏联特工
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.12,0:15:28.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有时他还被批评说先是个民族主义者
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:29.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,然后才是个共产主义者
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:32.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,然后他被派到了中国
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.58,0:15:36.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,组织起了一堆越南流亡分子
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.11,0:15:40.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并帮忙建立了印度支那共产党
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.77,0:15:42.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从始至终
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.86,0:15:44.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"他兢兢业业 谨小慎微"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:45.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,朋友这样回忆道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.86,0:15:47.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"心中只有一个念头
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:50.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他的国家 越南"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:10.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,到1940年 世界上大部分地方又陷入了战争
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.22,0:16:21.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,德国攻占了大部分西欧
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.76,0:16:23.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国也沦陷了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:28.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,日本帝国威胁到了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:31.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,欧洲在亚洲的许多殖民地
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.07,0:16:33.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并占领了越南
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.06,0:16:36.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们允许已经投降的法国盟友
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:39.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,继续监管他们的殖民地
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:44.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对有些越南人来说
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:47.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,日本人的到来似乎可喜地预示着
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.18,0:16:50.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,白人殖民者的统治即将结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:54.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但胡志明仍在中国流亡
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.38,0:16:57.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他把日本人也视作外来入侵者
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.40,0:16:59.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并没有比法国人好到哪去
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.41,0:17:03.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们只想着剥削他的国家
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:08.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,拿越南人的粮食去填饱自己的肚子
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.96,0:17:11.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,是时候了 他说
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.61,0:17:15.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,要召集 "所有年龄和所有类型的爱国者
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:19.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,农民 工人 商人和士兵"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:23.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,来抗击日本人和通德的法国人
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.94,0:17:29.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1941年2月
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.48,0:17:32.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在离开祖国30年后
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.24,0:17:36.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明偷偷越过中国边境回到了越南
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.86,0:17:41.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并在偏远的北坡村附近建立了总部
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:44.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这个村边的石灰岩山洞总部
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.11,0:17:46.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,被他叫做 卡尔·马克思洞
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.15,0:17:51.24,中文对白,,0,0,0,,山脚下的丛林溪流也以他的英雄命名
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.25,0:17:52.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,列宁溪
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:57.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在这里 他成立了一个革命运动组织
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.19,0:18:00.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他称之为 越南独立同盟
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.09,0:18:02.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,简称 越盟
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.29,0:18:19.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,为了打造和领导一支革命武装力量
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.64,0:18:22.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明叫来了武元甲
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:24.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武元甲曾是教法国历史的老师
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.93,0:18:28.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在河内教导过精英们的孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.45,0:18:32.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武元甲很早就接受了共产主义
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.19,0:18:35.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国人在监狱里把他的妻子殴打至死
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.60,0:18:38.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这加剧了他终身对法国人的血海深仇
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:43.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在拿破仑和阿拉伯的劳伦斯
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.56,0:18:47.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及中国共产革命者毛泽东的鼓舞下
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:51.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武元甲已经开始形成了一种独特的战争理论
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.97,0:18:54.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,即依靠游击战术
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.64,0:18:58.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,再静等时机发动全面的常规进攻
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.85,0:19:03.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他相信在即将到来的独立之战中
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:09.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他的军队将 "无处不在又无影无形"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.04,0:19:14.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南人总采取游击战是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:16.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们是一个小国家
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.39,0:19:20.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,通过这种方式就能以弱打强
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.32,0:19:25.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不打无把握之仗
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:29.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,出其不意 攻其不备
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:32.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,致人而不致于人
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.92,0:19:43.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那天我带了45人中的26人出来
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.38,0:19:45.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们总是有点儿寡不敌众
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.68,0:19:48.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但这天真的是太寡不敌众了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.82,0:19:51.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我的排队正在侦察
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:19:58.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,走 走 走 走 走
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:20:01.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,突然之间 最前头的侦察兵
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:03.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,队列中的那第一个人
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.12,0:20:06.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说 "路上有越共 路上有越共"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.29,0:20:11.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我还没来得及消化这讯息
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.19,0:20:13.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他就倒下了 胸口正中一枪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.41,0:20:19.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们发动了一场精心准备的埋伏
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.76,0:20:32.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我知道自己失去了很多兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:34.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我向上帝祷告说
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.03,0:20:36.00,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我说
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.42,0:20:39.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"如果你需要带走更多我排里的人
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:41.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那就带走我吧 别再带走我的兄弟了"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:42.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我一说完这话
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.53,0:20:45.00,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我都被自己吓到了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.02,0:20:48.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"妈的 我能收回那祷告吗"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.39,0:21:02.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,到1945年春天
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.43,0:21:07.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,日本偷袭珍珠港已经过去了3年多
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.37,0:21:11.50,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国政府正在寻找
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.51,0:21:13.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南战线上的盟友
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.72,0:21:15.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国人希望能找到方法
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.81,0:21:18.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,来破坏越南的日本军队
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.01,0:21:21.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这时胡志明联系上了他们
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.79,0:21:26.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们决定投放一支战略情报局队伍
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.83,0:21:29.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,去跟越盟领导层会面
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:34.54,中文对白,,0,0,0,,保罗·霍格兰是队里的医生
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.26,0:21:37.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他一到就马上被告知说
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:40.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他需要去见他们病重的领导
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.53,0:21:43.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所以他被带到了一个草棚里
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.78,0:21:48.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一个瘦弱的长着胡子的人就躺在草堆上
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.58,0:21:49.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,病得很严重
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.41,0:21:51.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那就是胡志明
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:58.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,战略情报局是中情局的战时前身
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.67,0:22:02.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们给胡志明的破烂游击队提供了武器
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:05.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并惊讶于他们很快地就学会如何使用了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.95,0:22:09.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明开始把自己的追随者们称作
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.60,0:22:11.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"越美联军"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.02,0:22:15.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并赞扬美国是 "民主的捍卫者"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.87,0:22:19.26,中文对白,,0,0,0,,且肯定能帮他们结束殖民统治
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:41.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,同时饥荒席卷着这个国家的北部
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.96,0:22:46.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,数十万越南人都快被饿死了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.20,0:22:50.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而日本人的仓库都还满是粮食
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.61,0:22:56.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那时期里 人们都推着车来收集垃圾
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:23:00.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我母亲还记得每天早上
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.58,0:23:03.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,她就会看到这些垃圾车出来街上
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.65,0:23:07.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,人们就会把尸体捡起来扔到车上
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.97,0:23:09.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那简直难以置信
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:13.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,经历了这一切的人永远也不会忘记
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.85,0:23:19.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杨文麦的父亲是河内东部某省的副总督
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.43,0:23:24.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他祖上两代都是为法国人效劳的官吏
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.86,0:23:27.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他跟夫人共育有17名儿女
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.66,0:23:33.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有着许多小孩的父母们
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.13,0:23:37.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都很担心自己的孩子会被偷走或杀死
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.19,0:23:41.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那就像是人间地狱
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:46.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,政府不知道要怎么应对这场灾难
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.63,0:23:50.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但胡志明知道
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.39,0:23:52.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他下令越盟尽可能地
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.56,0:23:55.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,闯进日本人的仓库
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.96,0:23:58.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,把库存的粮食发给民众
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.96,0:24:02.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们被誉为救世主
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.39,0:24:20.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,后来一颗原子弹摧毁了广岛
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.80,0:24:24.70,中文对白,,0,0,0,,3天后另一颗原子弹摧毁了长崎
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.92,0:24:27.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,日本人似乎马上就要投降了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.36,0:24:33.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明号召所有越南人奋起
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.12,0:24:35.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,接管他们自己的国家
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.25,0:24:37.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,免得自由法国会重建起
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.88,0:24:40.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,原有的殖民统治
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.27,0:24:45.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南人夺回了全国各地的城镇
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.76,0:24:51.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1945年9月2日
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.76,0:24:55.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这天日本正式投降了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.36,0:25:00.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,成千上万的越南人涌入河内的巴亭广场
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.85,0:25:05.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,首次见到了神秘的越盟领导人
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.96,0:25:10.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并听着他宣布越南独立了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.50,0:25:18.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有名战略情报局的官员也站在附近
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.69,0:25:23.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明以托马斯·杰斐逊的名言开场
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.04,0:25:25.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"人生而平等
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.60,0:25:31.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,造物主赋予他们若干不可剥夺的权利
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.63,0:25:34.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,其中包括生命权 自由权
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.12,0:25:37.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及追求幸福的权利"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.65,0:26:01.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明很期待
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.78,0:26:06.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国会支持越南的独立愿望
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.86,0:26:09.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不一定需要直接干预
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.83,0:26:12.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但美国可以尽可能地
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.88,0:26:15.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,支持他们的独立运动
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.57,0:26:20.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明指望美国的支持固然有自己的算盘
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.69,0:26:22.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但也无可厚非
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.62,0:26:27.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,罗斯福总统曾允诺过战后的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.37,0:26:30.26,中文对白,,0,0,0,,将会 "尊重所有民族选择
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.28,0:26:33.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,其生活所处的政府形式的权利"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.29,0:26:38.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但罗斯福现已离世
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.22,0:26:40.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他的继任者哈里·杜鲁门
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.60,0:26:43.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所接手的是一个很不一样的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.60,0:26:47.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,昔日打赢了二战的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.05,0:26:50.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美苏同盟如今已然解体
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.55,0:26:52.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,苏联现在侵占吞并了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.89,0:26:55.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一堆的东欧国家
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.83,0:26:58.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并想将其影响力进一步
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.69,0:27:02.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,扩散到伊朗 土耳其和地中海
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.91,0:27:06.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一场新的冷战开始了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.33,0:27:10.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国总统戴高乐警告说
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.91,0:27:13.21,中文对白,,0,0,0,,如果美国坚持要让
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.21,0:27:15.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法属殖民地独立的话
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.76,0:27:17.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国可能会别无选择
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.68,0:27:20.26,中文对白,,0,0,0,,只能 "成为俄国的卫星国"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.01,0:27:24.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国必须不能削弱阻碍
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.74,0:27:27.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法兰西帝国的恢复壮大
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.90,0:27:30.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,当然也不能动到越南
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.05,0:27:37.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在越南的美国人极少
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.55,0:27:39.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,只有国务院人员
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.22,0:27:40.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,领事馆官员
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.91,0:27:43.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及几个商人
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.17,0:27:45.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,几乎没有美国人
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.43,0:27:47.26,中文对白,,0,0,0,,会知道越南在哪里
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.05,0:27:51.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,乔治·威克斯隶属战略情报局的一个七人小队
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.92,0:27:55.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们被派到西贡 这是南边最大的城市
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.26,0:27:58.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国在官方上保持中立
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.86,0:28:01.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,希望法国和越盟能够
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.49,0:28:04.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,自行达成某种和解
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.22,0:28:09.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,盟国领导们同意暂时将越南
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.16,0:28:11.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,分成两个独立的区域
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.47,0:28:15.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,由中国国民党军接管北越的事务
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.81,0:28:20.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,英国殖民军也将在南越执行同样的任务
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.01,0:28:25.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但南越的敌对双方 法国和越盟
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.15,0:28:28.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,已经在西贡的街头打了起来
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.19,0:28:32.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,没有人能掌管大局
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.56,0:28:37.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,双方都是野蛮残暴
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.86,0:28:40.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那不能算是一场内战
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.50,0:28:44.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但在西贡街头越来越像是一场内战了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.86,0:28:49.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,28岁的中校彼得·杜威
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.09,0:28:51.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,是战略情报局在西贡的指挥官
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.73,0:28:53.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他想要理清这一切
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.15,0:28:57.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从一开始他就跟各方接触
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.14,0:28:58.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不只是法国人
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.35,0:29:01.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他还很快联系上了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.18,0:29:03.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南的各种团体
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.76,0:29:06.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越盟很快就主动地成为了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.63,0:29:08.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,联系最为密切的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.27,0:29:12.70,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜威讲着流利的法语
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.71,0:29:15.79,中文对白,,0,0,0,,斡旋于越盟的一名发言人
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.81,0:29:18.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,与城里的一名法国高级代表之间
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.28,0:29:24.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他的努力激怒了英国将军道格拉斯·格雷西
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.20,0:29:26.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,将军指挥着南边的盟国军队
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.68,0:29:30.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,格雷西相信应该
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.32,0:29:33.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,尽快恢复法国的控制
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.57,0:29:36.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,格雷西说正在和越盟谈判的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.56,0:29:40.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜威中校已经成了一个 "颠覆" 分子
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.32,0:29:46.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,西贡内外的暴力冲突变本加厉
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.66,0:29:50.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜威中校急忙发电讯给上级
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.81,0:29:54.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他写道 越南 "正在熊熊燃烧"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.59,0:29:57.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"法国人和英国人在这里已经没戏了"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.24,0:30:02.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他总结道 "美国也该离开东南亚了"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.23,0:30:07.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,两天之后
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.75,0:30:10.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1945年9月26日
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.19,0:30:13.07,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他出发前往机场
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.31,0:30:16.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,准备飞回战略情报局的总部
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.46,0:30:19.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在一处路障前
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.78,0:30:23.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越盟把杜威误认作法国人
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.11,0:30:24.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并开枪射击了
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.43,0:30:28.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他当场身亡
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.26,0:30:33.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明写信给美国
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.85,0:30:36.24,中文对白,,0,0,0,,向杜威之死表示哀悼
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.24,0:30:38.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他认可杜威
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.38,0:30:40.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,是一位同情他事业的人
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.66,0:30:45.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这对杜威来说似乎是个天大的讽刺
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.72,0:30:49.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他尽己所能地帮助越南的独立运动
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.06,0:30:53.07,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最后却阴差阳错地死在越南人手上
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.10,0:31:09.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一名非裔的美国老妇人来开门了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.22,0:31:18.50,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我想她一看到我们在那里就知道怎么回事了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.37,0:31:23.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,军队的牧师跟她说
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.70,0:31:28.07,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"我非常抱歉地通知您
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.10,0:31:32.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,您的儿子在越南阵亡了"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.41,0:31:36.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,她就只是坐了下来 一句话都没说
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.34,0:31:42.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,然后她的丈夫说 "不对 这肯定是弄错了"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.34,0:31:44.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他回去拿了这封信出来
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.30,0:31:46.00,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说 "看这 看到了吧
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.54,0:31:50.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,昨天才收到的信 我们儿子昨天都还活着"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.92,0:31:54.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,牧师看了下那封信
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.67,0:31:56.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说 "这是一周之前的了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.99,0:32:00.66,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我想您的儿子应该是在写信的同一天阵亡的"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.06,0:32:11.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1945年秋天
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.52,0:32:13.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜威中校死后一周
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.83,0:32:17.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,新补充进来的法军抵达了西贡
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.30,0:32:19.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,接替了原先的英国人
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.64,0:32:23.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们迅速控制住了这座城市
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.54,0:32:27.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并出发去重新占领整个国家
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.13,0:32:32.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明希望能找到某种方式既可实现独立
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.70,0:32:34.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,又不用跟法国开战
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.49,0:32:37.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他仍然希望美国能进行干涉
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.07,0:32:39.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"我们永远不会成为一个帝国
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.83,0:32:42.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,永远不会剥削亚洲人民"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.38,0:32:44.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他向到访的一名美国记者说道
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.25,0:32:49.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"不要被共产主义这个问题蒙蔽了双眼"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.10,0:32:54.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他不想把法国立成美国的敌人来打
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.03,0:33:01.54,中文对白,,0,0,0,,事实上 我看了他写给杜鲁门总统的信
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.10,0:33:05.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说 "我们所相信的正是你们所相信的"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.46,0:33:08.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我在中情局档案里看到的这些信
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.23,0:33:12.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,它们都未曾转交给过杜鲁门总统
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.67,0:33:19.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1946年6月
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.93,0:33:22.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明回到巴黎
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.06,0:33:24.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,徒劳地想要法国人
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.39,0:33:26.70,中文对白,,0,0,0,,兑现他们的承诺
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.71,0:33:29.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,提高越南的自主权
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.01,0:33:32.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明不在时
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.37,0:33:34.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武元甲将军开始巩固起
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.77,0:33:37.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,共产党对革命的控制了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.24,0:33:40.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他残酷地清洗了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.35,0:33:43.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,民族主义对手政党的成员
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.21,0:33:46.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有那些他所谓的 "反动破坏分子"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.76,0:33:49.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,地主和高利贷主
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.88,0:33:52.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,托洛茨基派和天主教徒
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.20,0:33:55.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有被控叛通法国的男男女女
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.49,0:34:00.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,上百人被枪杀 淹死和活埋
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.13,0:34:16.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1946年12月19日
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.86,0:34:19.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,经过数月的紧张加剧后
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.61,0:34:23.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越盟和法国在河内爆发了战斗
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.26,0:34:31.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最终越盟的火力不敌法国
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.11,0:34:41.21,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明和武元甲及其同志们跑到了城外
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.44,0:34:45.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,回到了他们远在北边的山间要塞
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.44,0:34:50.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"有枪的人会拿起他们的枪"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.72,0:34:52.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明在广播里号召
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.95,0:34:55.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,发动全国范围的游击战
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.49,0:34:59.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"有剑的人会拿起他们的剑
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.86,0:35:05.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,没有剑的人会拿起铁铲和木棍"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.06,0:35:38.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但是胡志明想要团结起来的这个国家
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.17,0:35:40.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,本身已经四分五裂了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.24,0:35:43.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,就连家庭也被撕裂了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.42,0:35:47.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,尽管父亲供职于法国政府
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.77,0:35:52.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杨文麦的姐姐仍觉得必须要回应胡志明的号召
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.64,0:35:59.07,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我的姐姐棠嫁给了一个
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.08,0:36:02.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,十分同情越盟的人
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.99,0:36:05.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那时胡志明已经把他的政府
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.62,0:36:07.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,转移到了山间的基地里
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.72,0:36:10.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所以我的姐姐和姐夫就一路
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.05,0:36:13.54,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从河内跋涉到那个基地
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.85,0:36:17.79,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以求加入反抗法国的队伍
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.78,0:36:22.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所以越战在家庭层面上
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.38,0:36:24.00,中文对白,,0,0,0,,确实是一场内战
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.46,0:36:35.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国派遣了成千上万人到越南
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.67,0:36:39.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国常规军 欧洲雇佣军
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.55,0:36:44.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有摩洛哥 阿尔及利亚 突尼斯和塞内加尔的殖民地军队
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.08,0:36:48.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,协同作战的还有缅甸军队
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.68,0:36:49.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,老挝军队
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.75,0:36:52.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及反共的越南人
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.61,0:36:58.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国军队设法占领了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.73,0:37:02.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,多数的大城镇和省会
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.38,0:37:06.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并建造了成百上千的独立前哨
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.73,0:37:12.21,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国还准备争取来越南的农民
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.22,0:37:15.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们为此开展了一项 "平息" 行动
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.79,0:37:17.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,安抚和解之意
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.45,0:37:20.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们修建堤坝 学校和道路
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.69,0:37:22.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,给孩童接种疫苗
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.66,0:37:28.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国人安抚了一座村子后
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.05,0:37:31.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们在白天能控制这村子
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.31,0:37:35.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但到晚上越盟就又回来了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.20,0:37:38.81,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所以永远不会有绝对的安全
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.73,0:37:43.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我父亲就摇头说道
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.28,0:37:45.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"平息行动真的是徒劳
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.34,0:37:49.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为这就像是要用手指去握住流沙"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.75,0:37:55.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越盟破坏道路
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.16,0:37:57.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,炸毁桥梁和铁路
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.06,0:38:00.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,伏击法国的巡逻队
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.50,0:38:03.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,然后消失无踪
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.64,0:38:09.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国士兵有时会报复最近的村庄
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.75,0:38:12.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,火烧房屋 奸淫妇女
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.63,0:38:16.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,处死有帮助越盟嫌疑的男人
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.37,0:38:57.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但是共产党的残暴
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.35,0:39:00.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也跟法国人不相上下
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.40,0:39:03.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"宁可错杀无辜"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.96,0:39:08.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有名同志如此说道 "不可放过一个"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.80,0:39:11.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们尤其针对那些
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.84,0:39:14.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,跟法国有所联系的人
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.07,0:39:17.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我父亲一旦开始为法国工作
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.97,0:39:19.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他马上就成了目标
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.63,0:39:21.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,尤其他官越做越大
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.76,0:39:23.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他这靶子就愈发明显
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.51,0:39:28.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有名越盟特工真的带了把手枪进来
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.91,0:39:30.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,准备开枪打他
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.06,0:39:32.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不过他在最后一刻放弃了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.52,0:40:15.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国人的伤亡数量持续上升
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.85,0:40:19.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"有些时候我们十分沮丧
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.24,0:40:21.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们甚至都想放弃算了"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.45,0:40:23.54,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一名法国士兵写信给母亲如此说道
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.82,0:40:25.79,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"我们的车队被伏击
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.80,0:40:27.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,道路被阻断
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.17,0:40:30.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,每晚都要向四面八方开火
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.47,0:40:32.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,国内对此漠不关心"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.33,0:40:45.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我在那里的时候 有时能打电话给我妈
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.64,0:40:50.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我跟我妈说那里发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.04,0:40:52.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我跟她说
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.07,0:40:56.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不要相信新闻和电视上说的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.29,0:40:57.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为我们正在输掉这场战争
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.85,0:41:01.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我说 "你可能再也见不到我了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.64,0:41:04.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为我们是陆战队里
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.39,0:41:06.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最北边的哨点"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.22,0:41:08.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们一探头就能看到北越了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.47,0:41:10.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们能看到对方枪口的焰火
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.88,0:41:13.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我说 "我队里的每个人都要死了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.93,0:41:15.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我可能回不去了"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.41,0:41:17.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我妈就说 "不会的 你会回来的"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.68,0:41:21.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,她说 "我每天都跟上帝祷告 你跟别人不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.60,0:41:23.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,你会回来的"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.29,0:41:25.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我说 "妈 每个妈妈都会觉得
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.85,0:41:27.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,自己的小孩是特例
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.68,0:41:31.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我就在把一些特例的遗骸装进尸体袋里"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.92,0:41:39.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜鲁门总统惊人地宣布说
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.65,0:41:41.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,俄国秘密拥有了原子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.12,0:41:44.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这引起了世界各国国务院的不安
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.16,0:41:49.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们很清楚地意识到这是场冷战
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.84,0:41:51.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们面对着一个敌人
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.62,0:41:54.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这敌人就是苏联
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.72,0:41:58.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国站在一个极点
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.87,0:42:01.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,苏联站在另一极点
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.10,0:42:04.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那就像是摩尼教里的动态平衡一样
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.12,0:42:06.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,世界上既有恶 也有善
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.22,0:42:08.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们是善的一方 另一方则是恶的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.80,0:42:11.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,双方泾渭分明
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.55,0:42:18.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,俄国成为有核力量才几星期
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.20,0:42:20.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,骇人的消息还将持续传来
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.72,0:42:25.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,毛泽东领导的共产力量控制了中国
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.12,0:42:30.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,互相独立的共产叛乱也席卷了
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.62,0:42:34.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,英国的缅甸和马来亚殖民地
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.02,0:42:38.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1950年1月
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.10,0:42:42.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,毛泽东正式承认胡志明的叛乱力量
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.24,0:42:45.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并同意提供胡志明所寻求的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.17,0:42:48.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武器装备和军事训练援助
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.68,0:42:51.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,苏联也承认了越盟政权
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.00,0:42:54.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并也提供援助
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.40,0:42:57.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜鲁门总统被政治对手
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.92,0:43:01.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,指责说他 "丢掉" 了中国
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.63,0:43:04.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而且没能 "遏制" 共产主义
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.47,0:43:07.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在他批准了一项2300万美元的援助项目
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.88,0:43:10.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,用来帮助越南的法军
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.28,0:43:14.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国不再中立了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.95,0:43:18.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们陷入了一种困境里
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.80,0:43:23.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们怎么能维持跟法国的友谊和同盟
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.11,0:43:25.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并在印度支那支持他们
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.56,0:43:28.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,同时作为前殖民地的我们
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.80,0:43:31.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还能同情越南人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.02,0:43:33.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对自由和独立追求?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.46,0:43:41.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一支训练有素 装备精良的北韩军队
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.26,0:43:43.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越过三八线来攻击了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.74,0:43:45.81,中文对白,,0,0,0,,措手不及的南韩守军
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.13,0:43:49.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1950年7月
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.45,0:43:52.66,中文对白,,0,0,0,,中国的盟友 共产主义北韩
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.67,0:43:54.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,入侵了南韩
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.47,0:43:59.26,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜鲁门总统指挥数十万的
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.28,0:44:02.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国地面部队进入了朝鲜半岛
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.99,0:44:11.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国及其盟友
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.04,0:44:13.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最终把入侵者赶回了北边
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.80,0:44:17.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,同时在中国南方
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.93,0:44:21.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,毛泽东的军队正开始把越盟
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.39,0:44:23.70,中文对白,,0,0,0,,改造成一支现代战斗部队
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.35,0:44:29.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,让他们有能力重创法国占领军
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.72,0:44:38.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜鲁门政府在7月份
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.14,0:44:40.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,悄悄地派出了数架运输机
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.63,0:44:43.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及一船的吉普车到越南
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.01,0:44:46.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有35名军事顾问随行
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.60,0:44:48.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,来监管这些物资的使用
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.69,0:44:54.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这些顾问和美国大使馆里的所有人
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.07,0:44:56.81,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都不会讲越南语
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.79,0:45:02.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但现在美国正式介入了越南
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.43,0:45:06.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1950年10月
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.89,0:45:09.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,成千上万的中国军队
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.85,0:45:12.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,开始涌入北韩
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.27,0:45:15.50,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并把盟军赶回了半岛后方
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.32,0:45:17.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,半岛激战之时
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.94,0:45:21.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,杜鲁门继续增加军事援助
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.48,0:45:24.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,支持在越南的法军
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.68,0:45:29.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,如果他们成功入侵了韩国
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.94,0:45:33.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那我们就等着赤潮传遍亚洲和欧洲
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.17,0:45:34.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,传到我们这个半球吧
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.57,0:45:39.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们在韩国打的仗
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.31,0:45:41.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,乃是为了我们国家的安全与生存
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.47,0:45:50.81,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1951年秋天
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.05,0:45:53.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一名年轻的马萨诸塞州议员
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.35,0:45:55.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,约翰·肯尼迪
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.10,0:45:58.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在马杰斯酒店的顶楼餐吧里一边吃着晚饭
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.57,0:46:00.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一边俯瞰着西贡
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.28,0:46:03.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他和党员们一边吃着
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.15,0:46:07.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一边听着枪声从西贡河对面传来
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.54,0:46:10.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法军指挥官向肯尼迪保证
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.00,0:46:13.54,中文对白,,0,0,0,,只要美国提供更多的援助
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.55,0:46:16.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国就能在这里恢复统治
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.82,0:46:20.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但肯尼迪和西默·托平待了两个小时
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.30,0:46:22.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,后者是经验丰富的美国记者
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.51,0:46:25.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他向肯尼迪讲了另一番故事
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.86,0:46:28.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说 法国正在失败
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.07,0:46:31.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而且许多曾经敬仰美国人的越南人
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.97,0:46:35.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也开始鄙视他们对法国的支持了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.94,0:46:39.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,肯尼迪相信了记者的说法
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.49,0:46:42.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,除非美国能够让越南人相信
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.98,0:46:46.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这就像是对抗共产主义那样
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.67,0:46:48.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在对抗 "不平等与不公正"
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.33,0:46:51.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他回国后跟选民说
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.49,0:46:55.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,目前的这些付出只能换来 "注定的失败"
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.57,0:47:07.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1952年
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.15,0:47:10.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,德怀特·艾森豪威尔将军当选总统
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.37,0:47:12.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一方面是因为他承诺
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.06,0:47:14.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,会更加强硬地对待共产主义
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.61,0:47:18.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,同年 美国的纳税者
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.98,0:47:21.81,中文对白,,0,0,0,,负担了法国在越南
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.82,0:47:24.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,30%多的军费
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.98,0:47:26.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在两年内
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.58,0:47:29.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这一数字变上升到了近80%
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.14,0:47:35.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,你们中的很多人都问到说
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.40,0:47:40.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,为什么美国要花费数百亿美元
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.63,0:47:44.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,去支持法兰西联邦的军队
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.48,0:47:47.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在印度支那抗击共产主义?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.30,0:47:50.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我想只要我们看一下这边的地图
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.54,0:47:53.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,你们就会知道它为什么那么重要了
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.43,0:47:55.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这里是印度支那
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.71,0:47:58.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,如果印度支那沦陷了
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.48,0:48:01.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,泰国也将难以为继
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.11,0:48:04.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,富产橡胶和锡的马来亚也将一样
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.81,0:48:09.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,就印度支那的战争而言
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.12,0:48:14.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我曾经到过那战场 或者也接近过那战地
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.13,0:48:17.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,它确实是一场血腥而艰苦的战争
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.78,0:48:27.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,到1953年 法国人已经打了7年了
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.62,0:48:30.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们付出了10万多人的伤亡
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.96,0:48:33.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也没能平息越南乡间
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.13,0:48:37.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,六任指挥官来了又走
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.95,0:48:40.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但是第七任司令官
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.20,0:48:43.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,亨利·纳瓦尔将军仍向法国国民
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.40,0:48:45.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,保证胜利在望
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.59,0:48:48.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说 "现在我们看到局势明了"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.28,0:48:51.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"就像是隧道尽头的光明一样"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.85,0:48:57.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,同时很多的法国民众
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.21,0:49:00.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都震惊于报道上所说的法军暴行
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.41,0:49:03.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及凝固汽油弹的大范围使用
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.99,0:49:05.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这种凝固汽油
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.12,0:49:07.79,中文对白,,0,0,0,,被用来焚烧丛林
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.81,0:49:08.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,村庄
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.99,0:49:10.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及人体肤肉
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.52,0:49:17.00,中文对白,,0,0,0,,当归国的法军士兵在马赛下船时
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.02,0:49:21.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,码头工会的成员们朝他们扔石头
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.88,0:49:24.86,中文对白,,0,0,0,,巴黎左派人士们开始称这场冲突为
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.88,0:49:27.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"肮脏的战争"
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.41,0:49:38.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那是一个特写镜头
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.84,0:49:41.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,拍到了一名警卫人员的肩膀
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.89,0:49:44.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有个孩子抓着他的领口
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.39,0:49:45.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他就把他砸倒在地
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.81,0:49:46.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,人们在尖叫...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.21,0:49:48.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在那个时候
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.54,0:49:51.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我意识到真正关心美国的人
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.68,0:49:53.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都已经被送到地球的另一端
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.38,0:49:55.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在丛林里追逐着一些牛鬼蛇神
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.12,0:49:59.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,同时我的国家被撕裂成两半了
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.86,0:50:02.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所以我才会看到一个跟我爸一样的人
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.32,0:50:04.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,殴打着一个跟我一样的人
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.64,0:50:06.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我该站那一队呢
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.99,0:50:16.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在韩国的三年战事结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.24,0:50:20.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,联合国与共产代表在板门店签约停战
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.56,0:50:22.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1953年7月
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.17,0:50:26.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,韩战以谈判解决而结束
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.74,0:50:28.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,留下了一个仍然分裂的半岛
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.59,0:50:32.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国的决策者认为这就证明了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.43,0:50:35.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,亚洲的共产主义是可以遏制的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.49,0:50:40.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那年秋天 法国人表示他们愿意
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.78,0:50:44.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,开启谈判以结束越南战事
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.66,0:50:47.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明同意了会面
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.69,0:50:52.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但在谈判代表齐聚日内瓦之前
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.81,0:50:57.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,双方都想在战场上改善己方的局势
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.86,0:51:01.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,纳瓦尔将军在越南西北部的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.70,0:51:04.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,偏远山谷里设立了森严的基地
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.74,0:51:06.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这就是奠边府
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.71,0:51:09.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他想把越盟引诱到这里
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.22,0:51:11.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,进行一场决定性战役
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.16,0:51:17.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,纳瓦尔相信法军的优势火力和空中支持
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.69,0:51:21.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,将碾碎越盟的一切进攻
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.69,0:51:24.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他和手下的军官们觉得不用担心
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.64,0:51:29.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,两边满是丛林的山丘俯瞰着他那
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.16,0:51:31.66,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在谷底挖坑道的1.1万人
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.94,0:51:36.51,中文对白,,0,0,0,,炮兵司令官信心满满
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.53,0:51:40.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他抱怨说 "我都用不到这么多火炮"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.11,0:51:45.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武元甲将军看到了可乘之机
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.33,0:51:49.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他回忆道 "我们决定不惜一切代价
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.62,0:51:53.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,肃清在奠边府的所有敌人"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:51:58.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,为此他发动了军事史上
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.23,0:52:01.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最大的一次后勤运动
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.18,0:52:04.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这次壮举在数十年里将会不断地
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.84,0:52:07.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,被搬上银幕 被人们庆祝
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.69,0:52:11.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,25万名平民搬运工
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.69,0:52:13.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,其中近一半为女性
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.40,0:52:16.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们搬运着他所需的一切围困物资
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.64,0:52:18.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从装米的麻袋
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.42,0:52:20.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,到火炮的零部件
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.98,0:52:23.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都被他们在丛林里徒步搬着
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.95,0:52:28.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武将军用5万名士兵围住山谷
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.77,0:52:31.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有200门大炮
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.04,0:52:34.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也都掩藏得很好
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.08,0:52:36.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从空中也不会被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.36,0:52:44.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1954年3月13日
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.16,0:52:46.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,山坡上的越盟火炮
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.89,0:52:49.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,开始每分钟倾泻下50发炮弹
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.85,0:52:52.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,炸在法军密密麻麻的山谷里
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.00,0:52:57.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,飞机跑道都被摧毁了
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.06,0:53:03.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,被困的法军只能通过空投来
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.15,0:53:05.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,补给兵力和物资
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.66,0:53:13.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,低估了敌军的法国炮兵司令
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.74,0:53:15.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,自杀身亡
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.36,0:53:19.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对奠边府的空中补给持续着...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.63,0:53:21.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,重要的人员和物资补给帮助了英勇的驻军
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.01,0:53:25.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,抵抗了越盟6个星期多的猛攻
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.41,0:53:28.07,中文对白,,0,0,0,,今天的奠边府就像是一座人类堤坝
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.10,0:53:29.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,努力地阻挡着赤潮
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.75,0:53:32.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,淹没整个东南亚
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.66,0:53:35.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国政府请求
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.31,0:53:37.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,艾森豪威尔总统进行干预
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.30,0:53:39.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,总统拒绝行动
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.67,0:53:44.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为没有国会的批准和欧洲盟友的支持
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.57,0:53:46.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,英国表示反对
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.87,0:53:50.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,国会也不会支持单方面的行动
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.16,0:53:53.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明领导的共产力量将会
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.43,0:53:55.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,获得他们所争取的独立
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.68,0:53:58.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而法国的战斗则是为了维持...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.19,0:53:59.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,维持殖民统治
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.90,0:54:01.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因此我认为
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.29,0:54:04.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在美国进行任何程度地介入之前
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.44,0:54:06.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那些人民应当获得独立
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.96,0:54:09.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们也理应支持这场斗争
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.18,0:54:14.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,艾森豪威尔在日记里坦诚道 "我认为
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.39,0:54:18.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这件事已经没有军事胜利的可能了"
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.19,0:54:21.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但是在未咨询国会的情况下
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.96,0:54:26.21,中文对白,,0,0,0,,总统仍秘密地派出了更多的美国运输机
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.24,0:54:31.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这些飞机修改了涂装并由民间承包商驾驶
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.69,0:54:36.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,用以补给在奠边府的绝望法军
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.97,0:54:42.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,大家都明白 就本身而言
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.60,0:54:45.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南并没那么重要
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.24,0:54:48.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但他们相信 我也相信
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.96,0:54:50.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,如果我们丢掉了越南
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.47,0:54:53.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,亚洲剩余的部分就将会倒向共产主义
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.21,0:54:58.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,更全面的考虑应遵循
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.17,0:55:02.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所谓的多米诺骨牌理论
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.22,0:55:05.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在有着一连串的多米诺骨牌
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.68,0:55:08.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,你推倒了第一块牌
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.70,0:55:11.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那么最后一块牌肯定
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.20,0:55:13.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也会很快地倾倒
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.30,0:55:39.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1954年5月7日下午
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.02,0:55:41.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在被困了55天后
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.85,0:55:46.66,中文对白,,0,0,0,,奠边府幸存的法军投降了
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.02,0:55:54.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们损失了8000人 包括阵亡 负伤和失踪的
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.06,0:56:01.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,武将军付出了3倍的伤亡代价
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.72,0:56:04.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但他取得了一场大胜
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.60,0:56:26.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这令杨文麦的父母也震惊不已
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.69,0:56:30.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们也很自豪于越盟能够打败
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.95,0:56:34.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国这一西方强国
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.05,0:56:37.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一方面是钦佩和敬重
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.89,0:56:40.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,另一方面则是恐惧
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.21,0:56:42.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而恐惧占据了上风
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.49,0:56:47.24,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"我们装逼不成反被打脸"
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.25,0:56:50.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,参议院少数党领袖林登·约翰逊如此说道
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.86,0:56:56.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"今天印度支那沦陷了 明天亚洲可能就陷入战火
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.08,0:57:01.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,后天西方盟国就成为废墟了"
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.35,0:57:04.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们应该把它看作是殖民时代
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.30,0:57:06.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在东南亚的终结
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.64,0:57:07.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,事实也是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.62,0:57:11.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但我们反而将之视为冷战时期
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.37,0:57:15.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们把它看作是自由世界的失败
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.47,0:57:17.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,把它跟中国崛起联系到一起
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.41,0:57:22.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这完全是一次对重大事件的误解
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.55,0:57:25.32,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也让我们付出了沉重的代价
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.12,0:57:34.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在国联的前总部 瑞士日内瓦
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.12,0:57:37.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,东西方将举行国际会议
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.10,0:57:40.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并可能决定亚洲的未来政治
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.05,0:57:44.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,奠边府战事结束之后
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.13,0:57:47.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,九个国家的外交官们齐聚日内瓦
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.58,0:57:49.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以解决越南的未来
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.51,0:57:55.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,谈判持续了近2个半月
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.07,0:57:59.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,虽然取得了胜利
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.58,0:58:03.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但胡志明和武元甲仍需要中国
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.28,0:58:07.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,和苏联的更多支持才能继续作战
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.51,0:58:12.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但中国已经在朝鲜损失了百万兵力
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.17,0:58:15.21,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们不想再卷进边境上的
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.23,0:58:16.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,另一场战争
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.62,0:58:22.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,苏联也正想跟西方缓和一下关系
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.46,0:58:26.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明的两大共产东家
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.19,0:58:29.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都催他同意谈判解决
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.65,0:58:33.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,接受跟结束韩战一样的分区治理
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.79,0:58:37.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明别无选择 只能屈服
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.25,0:58:44.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最后没人能满意而归
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.14,0:58:50.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南暂时以北纬17°线一分为二
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.13,0:58:55.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,北边法国所领导的13万军队
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.80,0:58:57.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,将会撤回到南边
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.99,0:59:02.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,大概5万到9万名越盟士兵
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.06,0:59:04.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也会 "重组" 回到北边
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.97,0:59:08.79,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一条中立区分隔了南北两边
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.98,0:59:11.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,直到能够举行选举
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.04,0:59:14.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,重新统一南北越南
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.92,0:59:19.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,每个人都知道胡志明将会赢得选举
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.34,0:59:55.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们开始往上走了
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.70,0:59:58.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们大概走到了山丘1/3高的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.15,0:59:59.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,然后他们开始袭击我们
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.66,1:00:04.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们就像是这块恐怖三明治的中间夹心
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.25,1:00:06.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们就这样叫它
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.61,1:00:15.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我在战争中学到了一件事情
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.74,1:00:17.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们不是这星球上的顶级物种
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.90,1:00:19.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为我们已经很客气了
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.52,1:00:25.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,人们常说军队如何把孩子
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.56,1:00:28.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,变成杀戮机器之类的
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.22,1:00:30.74,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而我总说这只是完成学业而已
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.72,1:00:40.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,开着摇晃的小船
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.99,1:00:43.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,勇敢面对危险的公海
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.41,1:00:45.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,上万名天主教和佛教徒
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.87,1:00:48.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,发现他们无法在共产主义下生活
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.35,1:00:50.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对他们来说 不自由无所有
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.77,1:00:56.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,根据日内瓦协议
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.74,1:00:59.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南两边的平民
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.99,1:01:02.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都可以在300天内
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.32,1:01:04.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,自愿搬到另一边
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.35,1:01:09.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我爸妈都想留下来
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.15,1:01:11.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,再次看看我姐姐棠
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.52,1:01:13.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为他们知道棠会回来的
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.63,1:01:16.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但另一方面他们又冒不起这个险
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.15,1:01:19.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明政府来到河内时
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.97,1:01:22.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们都被定为有罪了
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.59,1:01:26.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我的父亲将是第一个被杀死的人
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.39,1:01:28.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们所有人都会受到迫害
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.41,1:01:33.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我记得我们离开的那天
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.61,1:01:37.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我环顾了四周心想 "我再也回不来了"
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.12,1:01:41.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那是极大的创伤
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.07,1:01:46.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,突然间就无依无靠了
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.36,1:01:51.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最后大约有90万难民
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.29,1:01:55.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,包括一半以上居住在北边的基督教徒
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.45,1:01:57.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都逃往了南边
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.62,1:02:00.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们许多人登上了美国的船只
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.56,1:02:08.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国想以某种方式鼓励南越
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.23,1:02:10.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,建立起一个合法的政府
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.66,1:02:17.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在南越政府由吴廷琰领导
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.69,1:02:20.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他既是罗马天主教徒 也是孔教徒
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.27,1:02:22.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而这个国家里大多是佛教徒
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.47,1:02:24.38,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他是个单身主义者
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.38,1:02:27.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,曾经还想成为一名牧师
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.52,1:02:33.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们的战争始于我们开始跟他合作
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.01,1:02:38.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,或说是我们成为吴总统的受害者
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.10,1:02:44.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们要帮他把南越变成民主制
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.37,1:02:45.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说这就是他想做的
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.85,1:02:46.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们相信了他
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.70,1:02:49.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,和胡志明一样
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.15,1:02:52.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰也长年在国外寻求人们支持
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.86,1:02:56.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他个人版本的越南民族主义
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.54,1:02:58.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他从军中退伍后从事政治
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.45,1:03:00.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他对法国人的厌恶
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.88,1:03:03.72,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不亚于他对共产主义的痛恨
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.74,1:03:05.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,前者曾将他逮捕入狱
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.30,1:03:09.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,后者曾活埋他的长兄和侄子
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.03,1:03:13.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰既孤傲又独断
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.56,1:03:17.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不信任自己家族之外的任何人
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.59,1:03:20.94,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他也十分精明和机智
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.96,1:03:25.09,中文对白,,0,0,0,,善于利用对手的弱点
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.00,1:03:30.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但他面临着创建一个新国家的艰巨任务
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.22,1:03:35.79,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国人在南方仍驻扎着上万军队
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.80,1:03:37.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,且还不待见吴廷琰
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.35,1:03:41.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有几个省份仍受控于宗教派别
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.89,1:03:43.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,且拥有自己的军队
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.49,1:03:48.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,数十万的越盟士兵都回到了北方
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.48,1:03:50.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但仍有几千名骨干成员没回
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.59,1:03:53.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这些训练有素且献身共产党的工人们
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.01,1:03:58.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还留在南方的乡下组织抵抗活动
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.08,1:04:04.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,西贡则处在平川派的统治下
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.21,1:04:07.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这是受法国支持的一个犯罪组织
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.70,1:04:10.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国在平川派背后
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.20,1:04:11.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,类似于在支持他们
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.91,1:04:14.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为他们不想让吴廷琰得逞
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.64,1:04:17.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,于是这成了争论的焦点
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.55,1:04:20.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,中情局里的一些人认为
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.98,1:04:24.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰将会是南越的救世主
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.67,1:04:26.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,其他人则没这么确定
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.75,1:04:28.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"他可不是真正的救世主"
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.99,1:04:31.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,有位外交官向华府这样报告
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.77,1:04:35.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国大使也认同此言
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.75,1:04:39.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1955年4月27日
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.15,1:04:41.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,艾森豪威尔总统决定终止
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.92,1:04:45.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国对吴廷琰政权的支持
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.38,1:04:50.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但随后吴廷琰开始全面
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.61,1:04:52.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,进攻平川派
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.36,1:04:57.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,突然在那天中午
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.19,1:05:01.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们听见了枪声 看到了火焰
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.34,1:05:04.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,街区着火烧了起来
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.23,1:05:06.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,双方都有成百上千人的伤亡
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.83,1:05:09.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这场街头战斗持续了一整个星期
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.95,1:05:11.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,对美国来说
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.01,1:05:13.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这局势显然是一个严重的问题
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.07,1:05:18.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰最终取得了西贡的控制权
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.58,1:05:22.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,最后吴廷琰的部队胜利了
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.63,1:05:27.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,艾森豪威尔现在别无选择
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.46,1:05:29.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,只能绑定吴廷琰了
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.80,1:05:33.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,法国随后宣布说他们即将
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.67,1:05:37.24,中文对白,,0,0,0,,完全撤出南越
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.24,1:05:40.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,结束这近一个世纪的占领
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.32,1:05:44.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰变得很受欢迎
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.73,1:05:49.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为他似乎代表了南方的民族主义事业
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.92,1:05:51.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他成功地让法国人
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.79,1:05:53.85,中文对白,,0,0,0,,完全地离开了越南
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.86,1:05:57.37,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而胡志明只能让他们撤出北部半个越南
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.00,1:05:59.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,旗开得胜后
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.41,1:06:02.41,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰要求在南方举行公投
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.29,1:06:08.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,中情局警告他不要过于贪心地要回报
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.65,1:06:11.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但是在计算选票时
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.64,1:06:16.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰宣称他赢得了98.2%的选票
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.94,1:06:22.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1955年10月26日
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.59,1:06:26.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰宣布自己为全新的
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.03,1:06:29.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南共和国的第一任总统
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.05,1:06:36.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在日内瓦所承诺的统一南北的大选
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.13,1:06:37.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,将不再举行
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.67,1:06:42.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他成了我们的盟友
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.06,1:06:44.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,或说是我们的主人
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.29,1:06:47.70,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为我们过分关注于
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.71,1:06:50.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,阻止共产主义接管南越
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.20,1:06:54.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,于是我们没法任由他失败
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.11,1:06:58.39,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所以吴廷琰就开始调配我们了
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.47,1:07:00.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这就是一种典型的关系
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.74,1:07:03.11,中文对白,,0,0,0,,你需要自己能信任的盟友
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.12,1:07:06.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,来成为你的外交政策的中心装饰品
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.08,1:07:07.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们一下子就明白了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.19,1:07:10.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,于是小人掌大权
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.49,1:07:17.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,从远东来了位特殊的访客
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.16,1:07:19.73,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南的吴廷琰总统受到了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.75,1:07:22.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,艾森豪威尔总统少有的机场接待
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.93,1:07:25.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他将进行为期四天的国事访问
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.60,1:07:29.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴总统是美国在东南亚最坚实的盟友
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.43,1:07:32.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他将寻求增加对他国家的援助
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.07,1:07:34.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以抗击愈发严峻的共产主义压力
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.02,1:07:37.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们的总统将体谅地倾听他的请求
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.46,1:07:43.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,大多数民主党和共和党的政客
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.38,1:07:45.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在似乎都跟参议员肯尼迪
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.62,1:07:47.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一样改变了看法
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.09,1:07:51.12,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他说南越是 "我们的幼苗"
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.14,1:07:53.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,"我们不能抛弃他"
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.11,1:07:57.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,如果它失败了 那么美国就会 "担负责任
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.22,1:08:01.29,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们在亚洲的声望也会降到新的谷底"
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.92,1:08:06.80,中文对白,,0,0,0,,此前从未有过一个南越国家
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.82,1:08:09.54,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但美国人曾在新政期间
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.55,1:08:11.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,重建了国内的许多地方
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.00,1:08:14.18,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也曾通过马歇尔计划
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.20,1:08:15.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,帮助了西欧战后重建
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.09,1:08:20.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,相信再建个南越也不难
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.83,1:08:24.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,艾森豪威尔命令了
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.98,1:08:27.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,许多美国平民到南越
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.77,1:08:30.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,带去了各种经济发展计划
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.58,1:08:35.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他希望这能赢得越南人的民心
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.51,1:08:40.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但这些平民的数量总是
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.71,1:08:43.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,没有派去的军事顾问多
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.48,1:08:48.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,后者受命来帮吴廷琰现代化训练和装备军队
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.23,1:08:52.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在他的军队叫做越南共和国军
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.44,1:08:53.50,中文对白,,0,0,0,,简称 南越国军
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.06,1:08:58.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一些国军军官发现美国人的方法
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.46,1:09:04.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并不适用于他们与共产党的游击战
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.22,1:09:06.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,大多数的美国军事顾问
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.55,1:09:08.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,都是韩战老兵
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.12,1:09:12.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们决心要让南越国军准备好
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.47,1:09:16.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,抵挡住北方的常规入侵
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.53,1:09:21.76,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但北越从来就没有
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.77,1:09:24.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,准备进行常规入侵
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.69,1:09:29.47,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明正着眼于重建他的
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.48,1:09:32.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,饱受了十多年的战争摧残的国家
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.04,1:09:39.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,共产党进行了残酷的土地革命
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.36,1:09:41.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,仿照的是中国正在进行的土改
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.79,1:09:45.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这无情地导致了数千人的死亡
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.91,1:09:49.96,中文对白,,0,0,0,,其中既有支持法国的地主
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.97,1:09:53.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,也有许多和越盟并肩作战的村民
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.55,1:10:00.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明仍决定要重新统一越南
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.39,1:10:04.59,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不过他担心对南方直接采取军事行动的话
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.69,1:10:08.52,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国将会更深地介入到这场斗争里
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.18,1:10:11.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他告诫南方的同志
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.57,1:10:14.36,中文对白,,0,0,0,,要相信政治煽动的力量
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.37,1:10:16.19,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并避免暴力手段
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.20,1:10:21.50,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但这消息听来却有些空洞
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.51,1:10:24.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,因为四面楚歌的南方革命者正挣扎着
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.49,1:10:28.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,活过吴廷琰日益严苛的政权
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.39,1:10:34.99,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在一场所谓的 "谴责共党" 运动中
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.00,1:10:39.77,中文对白,,0,0,0,,吴廷琰未经审判就逮捕了上万名平民
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.05,1:10:43.53,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并下令处死了上百人
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.06,1:10:48.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在这些共产党人决定自行做主
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.88,1:10:52.71,中文对白,,0,0,0,,开始攻击南越的官员
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.11,1:11:36.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,随着南越的暴力冲突加剧
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.45,1:11:39.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,河内出现了新的领导层
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.78,1:11:43.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,胡志明仍是面向世界的革命门面
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.50,1:11:46.67,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但他现在要把权力分享给
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.68,1:11:50.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,那些对他的谨慎越来越没耐心的人
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.84,1:11:54.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,美国对这些新人几乎一无所知
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.58,1:11:59.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,其中最重要的一名是个木匠的儿子
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.71,1:12:04.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他来自南方的广治省 名叫黎筍
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.62,1:12:09.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他曾帮助创立了印度支那共产党
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.36,1:12:12.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在法国监狱里待了近十年
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.59,1:12:15.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他是一个精明的政治斗争者
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.91,1:12:19.66,中文对白,,0,0,0,,所以一路升至党内第一书记
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.10,1:12:55.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,到1959年
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.87,1:12:58.50,中文对白,,0,0,0,,黎筍和他的强硬派盟友
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.51,1:13:02.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在北越政治局里的影响力越来越大
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.42,1:13:04.87,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并开始改变了北越的政策
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.19,1:13:10.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们争论说河内应该用尽一切力量
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.36,1:13:14.90,中文对白,,0,0,0,,帮助南越的革命同志武力除掉吴廷琰
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.14,1:13:39.93,中文对白,,0,0,0,,现在40到50支武装的越盟小队
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.94,1:13:43.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,开始偷偷溜进南越
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.48,1:13:47.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们所走的老挝山区的丛林小道
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.44,1:13:51.65,中文对白,,0,0,0,,将很快地被美国人称作胡志明小道
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.21,1:14:00.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,针对吴廷琰政权的暴力活动稳步上升
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.85,1:14:14.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1959年7月8日晚上
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.48,1:14:15.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在边和市
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.85,1:14:18.45,中文对白,,0,0,0,,就在西贡东北方20英里外
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.46,1:14:21.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,6名美国顾问正在他们的
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.12,1:14:23.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,食堂里看着电影
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.05,1:14:29.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越盟的游击队员悄悄地溜进基地里
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.09,1:14:31.15,中文对白,,0,0,0,,通过窗户向内开火
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.60,1:14:39.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,来自内布拉斯加州彭德的少校戴尔·比伊斯
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.65,1:14:44.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,和来自德州科珀勒斯科夫的军士长切斯特·奥文南
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.37,1:14:45.55,中文对白,,0,0,0,,中弹身亡
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.51,1:14:49.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们是越南战争中第一批
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.94,1:14:53.58,中文对白,,0,0,0,,死于敌军火力的美国士兵
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.52,1:15:00.21,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们站在一个最为显眼的舞台上
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.22,1:15:03.75,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们必须在举世共睹下再次证明
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.77,1:15:07.78,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这个国家是否还有人们所认为的
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.79,1:15:14.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,选择的自由 广泛的机会 抉择的范围
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.51,1:15:18.68,中文对白,,0,0,0,,来抗衡共产主义制度的坚决推进
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.67,1:15:22.31,中文对白,,0,0,0,,1960年11月8日
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.31,1:15:27.13,中文对白,,0,0,0,,约翰·菲茨杰拉德·肯尼迪当选为美国总统
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.14,1:15:30.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他的副总统是参议员林登·约翰逊
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.57,1:15:35.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,他们险胜了副总统理查德·尼克松
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.04,1:15:38.00,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及搭档参议员亨利·卡伯特·洛奇
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.98,1:15:43.10,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在竞选中 肯尼迪和尼克松都
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.12,1:15:47.21,中文对白,,0,0,0,,承诺会坚守对抗国际共产主义的阵线
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.31,1:15:49.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,而不管它是否有威胁性
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.82,1:15:54.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但很少有美国人知道或关心
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.18,1:15:57.04,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.40,1:16:00.88,中文对白,,0,0,0,,肯尼迪当选六周后
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.89,1:16:03.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在靠近柬埔寨边境的一座
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.62,1:16:05.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,偏远丛林山村新立村
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.90,1:16:09.05,中文对白,,0,0,0,,南越革命团体的代表们
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.09,1:16:13.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,齐聚建立一个新组织以取代越盟
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.48,1:16:16.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,并致力于推翻吴廷琰
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.66,1:16:19.57,中文对白,,0,0,0,,赶走支持他的外国人
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.29,1:16:26.16,中文对白,,0,0,0,,背后里 黎筍及其在河内的同志
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.18,1:16:28.35,中文对白,,0,0,0,,策划着这一切
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.36,1:16:32.63,中文对白,,0,0,0,,这个新组织将叫做
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.65,1:16:34.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,民族解放阵线
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.23,1:16:36.91,中文对白,,0,0,0,,简称 南民解
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.57,1:16:41.06,中文对白,,0,0,0,,南民解的军队叫做
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.09,1:16:43.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,人民解放武装力量
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.92,1:16:47.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但其在西贡和华府的敌人们
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.46,1:16:49.49,中文对白,,0,0,0,,更喜欢蔑视地称呼他们
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.41,1:16:53.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,在他们眼中 这些革命者都是
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.06,1:16:56.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,越南国家的共产主义叛徒
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.56,1:16:59.82,中文对白,,0,0,0,,简称 越共
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.49,1:17:50.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,让每个国家都知道
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.93,1:17:55.56,中文对白,,0,0,0,,不论它们希望我们繁荣还是衰落
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.19,1:17:59.14,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我们会付出一切代价
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.09,1:18:02.24,中文对白,,0,0,0,,承受一切负担
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.25,1:18:05.33,中文对白,,0,0,0,,迎接一切艰难
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.77,1:18:08.08,中文对白,,0,0,0,,支持一切朋友
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.10,1:18:10.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,反对一切敌人
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.93,1:18:14.26,中文对白,,0,0,0,,来确保自由的存在与胜利
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.27,1:18:29.20,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我一直以为勇气是
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.22,1:18:31.30,中文对白,,0,0,0,,冲进敌人堡垒
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.30,1:18:33.69,中文对白,,0,0,0,,或屹立于炮火中
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.35,1:18:36.54,中文对白,,0,0,0,,但光是走起来
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.20,1:18:39.79,中文对白,,0,0,0,,一天天地走 从这村到那村
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.82,1:18:43.42,中文对白,,0,0,0,,穿过稻田 爬上山林
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.77,1:18:48.62,中文对白,,0,0,0,,光是早上起来 望向大地
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.72,1:18:52.23,中文对白,,0,0,0,,想着 "过几分钟我就会走到那里了
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.26,1:18:55.28,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我的尸体会不会就倒在那里呢
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.80,1:18:57.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我会在外面那里失去一条腿吗"
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.55,1:19:02.03,中文对白,,0,0,0,,光是走起来就觉得非常勇敢了
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.76,1:19:05.44,中文对白,,0,0,0,,我有时走路会看着自己的双脚
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.47,1:19:07.61,中文对白,,0,0,0,,想着我怎么会来做这个呢
